title: cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add to cottage cheese along with the whip cream and pudding.
Garnish with cherries.

title: shrimp and green noodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Shrimp in one layer in bottom of baking dish with salt and pepper.
Saute mushrooms in 3 tablespoons butter and mix with flour and sour cream, 4 tablespoons butter, soy sauce and salt and pepper.
Pour all of sauce over shrimp. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake 10 minutes until bubbly.
Serve over cooked, drained green spinach noodles.

title: caramel cereal pops
directions: In heavy 3-quart saucepan, combine caramels and milk.
Cook and stir over low heat until caramels are melted and smooth.
Stir in the cereal and peanuts until well coated with caramel mixture. Press the cereal mixture into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Let stand about 1 hour or until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Insert a wooden stick into one end of each square.
Makes 16 pops.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Spoon into pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool slightly before cutting into squares.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: stuffed shells(with spinach-ricotta filling)
directions: Cook shells as directed.
Drain and rinse.

title: zucchini creole
directions: Simmer onion in butter in skillet.
Add tomatoes and squash. Cover.
Cook until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Season and serve.

title: spinach artichoke casserole
directions: Artichokes go on bottom.
Cover with spinach, salt and pepper. Beat cream cheese, butter and milk; spread over top.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: whiskey sour
directions: This recipe becomes a whiskey, rum or brandy sour if the base is changed.
Shake, using 3/4 cup cracked ice.
Strain into chilled glasses.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O completely in boiling water, stirring 3 minutes. Add lemon juice, lemon rind and ice cubes and stir constantly until Jell-O is thickened, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whisk, blend in Cool Whip, then whip until smooth.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound. Spoon into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish as desired.

title: rice dressing
directions: Gently boil giblets for approximately 2
hours or until done. Cool
and chop giblets and meat
from
necks.
Discard bones and skin, reserve liquid and add enough
to
equal 2 1/2 cups.	Brown rice in margarine, add vegetables and saute until onion is clear. Add giblets, turn into
a
covered casserole, add
salt, pepper and red pepper, mixing well.
Bake	at
350° approximately	1 1/2 hours or until rice is
done.
Stir
once during the baking process.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage cold slaw
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Separate broccoli into flowerets.
Chop green onions.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Mix together.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease dish.
Line bottom with 6 slices of bread (cut off crust).
Put 6 slices of American cheese on top of bread.
Blend eggs, milk, salt, instant onion and dry mustard.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Set 5 minutes.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Then top with sliced tomatoes and partially cooked bacon or sausage.
Broil until done.

title: three pepper stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
Sprinkle meat with salt, pepper and garlic.
Roll in flour.
Brown meat slightly in oil.
Remove meat and drain.
Add onions and mushroom soup and water.
Mix well.
Place meat, mushrooms and onions in mixture.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add bell pepper strips.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Garnish with parsley, tomatoes and mushrooms. Serves 5 to 6.

title: congealed deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs; cool and grate coarsely.
Mix cold water with gelatin.
Heat until dissolved and set aside.
Mix salad dressing, lemon juice, salt, pepper and relish.
Mix all ingredients into gelatin and chill until firm.

title: spiced cider
directions: Combine sugar, water and seasonings in 4-cup measure. Microwave at High for 4 to 6 minutes to form a light syrup. Combine with cider in 3-quart casserole dish.
Microwave for 7 to 9 minutes until heated.
Strain before serving.
Makes approximately 2 quarts.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, jam and applesauce.
Add soda to buttermilk and alternately add buttermilk and flour.
Add spices, raisins, dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 plus minutes.

title: baked shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together
except
3/4 cup cheese. Place in
2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: polly cakes
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and nuts.
Stir to mix well.
Fill paper baking cups half full in muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes a dozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Add one cup flour at a time, beating well after each cup.
Beat until real smooth and fluffy.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn heat to 350° and bake for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: clara stack's strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve jello in one cup boiling water.
Add partially thawed strawberries, allow to soft set.
Meanwhile roll cheese into balls and roll in finely chopped nuts.
Add cheese balls and any unused nut pieces to jello.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour in Bundt cake pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, veggies, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Lay out crescent rolls.
Cut into strips to lay on casserole (form lattice top).
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake 3 to 5 minutes longer.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Pour boiling water over ingredients and stir.
Cool.
Use in place of sweetened condensed milk in any recipe at a fraction of the cost.

title: nojim beef enchilada
directions: Brown ground beef and drain the oil.
Add minced dry onion to the ground beef and mix.
Add chopped olives and chili con carne, then mix all together real well.
Cook mixture and set aside.

title: potato breakfast casserole
directions: Cover hash browns with hot water; let stand 10 minutes and drain.
Lightly brown sausage; drain.
Beat eggs; add potatoes and remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: tuna noodles casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole.
In casserole, combine all ingredients except potato chips and butter or margarine.
Combine chips and butter and sprinkle over the casserole top.
Bake, uncovered, about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy; gradually stir in flour. Add vanilla and pecans; blend well. Refrigerate 2 hours, then roll into small balls. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden. Cool for 5 minutes, then roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar and eggs for 5 minutes. Slowly beat in salad oil, then flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and extract until well blended.
With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until done. Cool, then remove from pan.
Cover with Apple Glaze.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: vegetable-rice salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add rice, peas, carrots and onion and toss.

title: home canned pimientos
directions: Peel peppers; pack in pint jar, add salt.
(They make some liquid, add small amount of water if needed.)
Seal jar.
Place in pressure cooker; bring pressure up to 5. Turn stove off.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all this together; blend good.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo in pan.
While still hot, pour the batter in pan with melted butter. Then put peaches on top of this batter last.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until brown or until a knife comes out clean from cobbler.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and shape into balls.
Roll in flour and brown in oil.
Pour package of onion soup mix over browned meat balls.
Add 2 cups of water and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: butterhorns
directions: Dissolve
yeast
and
tablespoon
sugar
in lukewarm water. Combine
remaining
ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator overnight. Divide
dough into 3 sections; roll 1/4-inch thick and cut into 16 pie wedges each.
Roll each section from large end and cover with plenty of butter.
Let raise 2 hours.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Combine hot water (or milk), honey, salt and butter.
Cook to lukewarm.
Add beaten eggs and yeast.
Add flour and knead until well mixed.
Cover and let rise.
Punch down and let rise again.
Shape into 5 loaves.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: delicious dirty rice(yield: 4 side dish servings)
directions: Brown hamburger over medium heat, stirring to break up meat, until browned. Drain grease. In same pan, saut garlic, onions, green peppers and celery in butter until onions are soft and opaque. Add cooked rice and cayenne pepper. Simmer over low heat until rice has absorbed liquid. Stir in parsley and green onion; salt and pepper to taste.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Preheat shortening in large pan.
Combine butter, sugar, egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Blend in butter.
Use teaspoon to put into preheated shortening.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side.

title: chicken n dumplings
directions: Boil leg quarters in 4 quarts of water until done.
Place on plate to cool.
Save broth.
In a large mixing bowl, sift flour, leaving a depression in center.
In depression, place butter and pour in milk.
Gently knead until well blended.
Add flour and continue kneading until stiff dough forms.
Add flour until no longer sticky.

Lightly flour counter and roll out dough to 1 inch thick for thick dumplings and 1/2 inch thick for thin dumplings. Cut dough into 1/2-inch strips and cut into bite size pieces. Bring chicken broth to boil; add salt and pepper.
Drop in dumplings.
Bone chicken; chunk into pieces and cook with dumplings until thickened.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom.
Place rolls on top of nuts.
Sprinkle dry pudding over frozen rolls. Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add sugars and cinnamon.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over rolls in pan.
Cover and let rise overnight.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove and invert onto serving plate.
Makes 24 buns.

title: corn salad
directions: Chop onions and cucumber.
Combine all in a large bowl.
Chill overnight.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fat free pineapple upside cake
directions: Spray 9-inch round cake pan with Mazola cooking spray.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and lemon juice, stir to combine.
Place in 350° oven for 3 minutes.
Arrange pineapple rings and cherries in pan; set aside.
In large bowl, combine flour, cornstarch, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl, stir sugar and milk until sugar is dissolved.
Add egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla, stir until blended.
Gradually add to flour mixture; pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Immediately loosen edges and remove from pan.
Makes 12 servings.
Each serving:
200 Calories, 2 grams protein, 47 grams carbohydrates, 0 mg. cholesterol, 160 mg. sodium.

title: baked apple princess
directions: Peel each apple 1/3 the way down from top.
In individual custard cups, place 1 apple and 1/4 cup of ginger ale.
Sprinkle each apple with 2 teaspoons sugar cinnamon.
Bake covered at 375° for 35 minutes or until soft, not mushy.
Place 2 teaspoons of margarine in center of each apple.
Bake 1 more minute or until margarine melts.

title: linguine with chicken scampi
directions: Cook pasta.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch pieces.
Dip chicken into beaten egg, then bread crumbs which have been mixed with salt and pepper.
Spread coated pieces on platter.
(This can be done several hours ahead and refrigerated.)

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 1-inch pan, layer pineapple, cherry pie filling and dry cake mix.
Cut butter and place over cake mix.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients by hand and bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, checking often.
After cake has cooled, combine
cream cheese, powdered sugar, butter and vanilla.
Mix well and frost cake.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Layer apples in pie shell.
Mix together apple juice, cinnamon, nutmeg and cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Cook on low heat until thickened.
Pour over apples and place second pie crust on top.
Butter lightly and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: angel biscuits(thanksgiving - christmas special)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Cut into shortening.

title: congo cookie bars
directions: Mix well.
Pour and shape flat onto one large cookie sheet. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
When done, cool and cut into finger length bars.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Turn into oiled loaf pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In a large bowl, combine the corn, eggs, milk, 3/4 cup cracker crumbs, margarine, sugar, onion, salt and pepper. Transfer to a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: salmon spaghetti
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
Add undrained salmon and wine; simmer for 3 minutes.
Stir yogurt, cornstarch, pepper, parsley and garlic together; add to skillet and cook for 3 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti; sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: baked crab
directions: Make white sauce by melting butter in small saucepan; stir in flour.
Gradually add milk.
Combine crab meat, eggs and slivered almonds in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour white sauce over crab mixture.
Stir to cover well.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash, drain and hull berries.
Simmer 1 cup water with 2/3 cup of strawberries and cornstarch for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. While cooling, spread cream cheese over bottom of pie shells. Put remaining berries in pie shells.
Cover with cooked mixture. Refrigerate until firm (2 hours).
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches, reserve syrup.
Combine peach syrup, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon sticks and cloves in a saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour hot syrup over peaches and let cool.
Chill before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: baked pork chops and dressing
directions: Use large frying pan. Trim fat from pork chops. Brown chops in small amount of fat. Season with salt and pepper. Remove chops from pan. Cook celery and onion in butter until tender but not brown. Add water, soup mix and sage. Simmer 6 minutes. Add bread cubes; stir until moistened. Turn into 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Top with browned chops. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pasta with broccoli in sweet tomato sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the broccoli in enough boiling unsalted water to cover until just tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Rinse under cold running water, drain and set aside.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain completely.
Rinse slightly and let cool. Chop onion and celery; add to macaroni in a large bowl.
Add tuna to
vegetables; mix.
Add lemon juice and mix again.
Add mayonnaise, parsley, peas, salt, pepper and seasoning to bowl and mix.
Chill; serve cold.

title: white chili
directions: Cook and stir onion, garlic, cumin and oregano in olive oil in large saucepan until onion is tender.

title: cheese hominy casserole
directions: Drain hominy and corn.
Put soup, Cheez Whiz and onions in boiler. Heat until cheese melts. Remove and pour over hominy and corn. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch dish. Top with corn chips. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickle meat
directions: Mix together for 100 pounds to 120 pounds of meat.
Cut meat into squares.
Rub mixture all over meat.
Pack in stone jar. Put a weight on top.
Brine will cover meat.
Let set about 2 or 3 weeks. When ready to eat, slice and roll in flour and fry as chicken.

title: peanut butter rice krispies
directions: Melt almond bark with peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Put into buttered jelly roll pan.

title: seven layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce and place in bottom of 9 x 12-inch glass pan. Add next 6 ingredients in layers.
Beat dressing mixture with mayonnaise and sugar.
Put dressing on top of other ingredients. Cover with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: can't lose corn pudding
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, mix together eggs, milk, cream, butter and red pepper sauce; mix well and set aside.
Put corn in another mixing bowl and sprinkle with flour, sugar and salt.
Stir to coat corn.
Add the corn mixture to the egg mixture and stir.
Pour mixture into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until set.
Stir the pudding 3 times at 15 minute intervals while baking.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: o. j. pound cake
directions: Grease and flour bundt or angel food cake pan.
Pour nuts over bottom.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Mix well.
Pour batter over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool.
Glaze with the following recipe.

title: italian cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in rind from 1 orange and its juice.
Add almond extract and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixed with baking powder.
Bake at 375°.
Do not brown. Ice with confectioners sugar icing.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar;
mix well.
Add pumpkin, water and oil; mix again.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
For baking, use 1 pound coffee or other similar size cans.
Do not grease cans. Pour mixture into cans, fill to halfway mark.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven, turn cans upside down and let stand until cold.
Bread will slide easily from can.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all together in greased bread pan.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.

title: hamburger and macaroni
directions: Fry up your hamburger; drain.
Cook your macaroni, but not too done; drain.
Add your hamburger and tomato juice.
Cook until hot.

title: pumpkin bread(for bread machine)
directions: Add all ingredients in the order listed.
Select white bread or light button on bread machine and push the start button.

title: baked fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit; save juice.
Arrange fruit in a large casserole dish.
(Alternate fruit to produce color effect.)
Set aside. Melt margarine in pan.
Blend in flour, fruit juice and sugar. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat. Add sherry.
Pour over fruit. Garnish with cherry halves.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve hot to accompany main dish.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, hamburger and onion.
Add beans.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients and cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each.
Add vanilla.
Crush crackers fine.
Add to first mixture with baking powder, milk and coconut.
Mix well. Pour into 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: roquefort cheese dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Blend with a little of the oil. Stir in remaining oil, alternating with lemon juice.
When ready to serve, add cheese.

title: taste tartar sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: memphis cherry pie
directions: Whip together whipping cream, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix in 1/2 cup chopped almonds.
Pour cream cheese mixture into shell. Chill until firm.
Top with cherry pie fillings and remaining almonds.

title: banana cake
directions: Mash bananas.
Mix all ingredients together in a mixing bowl. Grease and flour a Bundt, sheet or two 9 x 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool for 30 minutes or until well cooled before taking out of pan.

title: pralines
directions: Mix brown sugar and whipping cream in a deep, microwavable bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Cook on High in microwave for 11 minutes and 45 seconds.
Stir in butter.
Add pecans.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Use medium cucumbers.
Wash and cut them into sticks.
Pour boiling water over them; let stand overnight.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In saucepan bring to a boil butter, oil, cocoa, and water. Sift together flour and sugar. Pour chocolate sauce over dry ingredients and mix well. Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda, and vanilla. Pour into a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cream chicken(kay honecker's mother's recipe)
directions: Cook onion and butter until tender.
Blend in flour, slowly stir in broth and cream.
Add spices, cook and stir over medium heat until it thickens.
Stir small amount hot mixture into egg yolks; return to hot mixture.
Cook over low heat 1 minute.
Add chicken and heat until hot throughout.

title: thanksgiving tomorrow
directions: Heat oven
Combine all ingredients, adding turkey broth or water if mixture is too dry.
Place in lightly greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until hot and lightly browned on top.

title: frozen nesselrode mousse
directions: In a large bowl let egg whites warm to room temperature.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat at high speed until soft peaks form. Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue to beat until stiff peaks form.

title: hot chinese chicken salad
directions: Roll chicken in cornstarch.
Heat corn oil in frypan.
Add chicken and brown quickly.
Sprinkle garlic powder.
Add tomato, water chestnuts, mushrooms, onions and celery.
Season with salt, pepper or spice of choice.
Add soy sauce.
Stir and reduce heat to simmer and cook 5 minutes.
Lightly toss chicken mixture with lettuce.
Serve hot with rice.
Serves 4.

title: wolverines
directions: In a medium bowl, combine powdered sugar and salt; stir in peanut butter.
Add vanilla, stirring until blended.
Shape into tsp. size balls and dip into chocolate.
Refrigerate 20 minutes to harden.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bonty-hoss
directions: Clean head and saw in pieces.
Cover all meat listed with water; cook until done.
Cool.
Remove all bones, then skin tongue.
Cut all meat into small pieces.
Now, to make the Bonty-Hoss!

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger or turkey meat in a heavy saucepan & drain. Combine Rotel sauce, hamburger & cheese.

title: parmesan broiled tomatoes
directions: Halve tomatoes crosswise and sprinkle with salt and pepper and a generous pinch of sugar.
Top each with about 1/2 teaspoon Parmesan cheese and dot with 1/2 teaspoon butter.
Broil about 6-inches from heat for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: sister's broccoli bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into iron skillet that has been greased and mealed (1 tablespoon meal).
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pina colada cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, margarine and coconut.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Drain pineapple in large bowl, beat cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Stir pineapple, sour cream, rum and coconut extract into cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Top with Pineapple Topping.

title: celery seed fruit dressing
directions: Mix together sugar, dry mustard, salt, onion and 2 tablespoons of vinegar.
Add the salad oil slowly, beating constantly.
Add the remaining 3 tablespoons vinegar and the celery seed.
Continue beating until dressing is thick.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups dressing.
May be used on lettuce salad.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bones.
Cut into small pieces. Saute onions and celery in 1/2 cup butter for 5 minutes.
Mix into bread with about 1 cup broth and 1 teaspoon salt.
Place into greased baking dish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix with hand mixer milk and pudding mixture.
Add butter, sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Break up Oreos into a fine powder.

title: jennifer's carrot cake
directions: Stir all together and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: monterey chicken
directions: Bake chicken at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven. Brush with barbecue sauce and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese melts. Sprinkle with bacon, onion and tomato and serve.

title: one egg cake
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and well beaten egg.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to first mixture with milk.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two 8 or 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This was my grandmother's recipe.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons liquid.
Combine sugar and flour and stir in reserved juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into 1-quart buttered casserole dish.
Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until light brown.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry orange mold
directions: Or use 1 cup each diced orange sections and chopped apple.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix sugar, butter and syrup together. Bring to a boil. Remove and add peanut butter and corn flakes. Spoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Rinse frozen shrimp. Remove tails. Saut shrimp in margarine until hot. Add tomatoes. Simmer together. Serve over rice.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: *Whole tomatoes are best when chopped up.

title: toll house oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Blend butter, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats and chocolate.
Drop by rounded half teaspoons on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles until they are done; drain.
Run under cold water and drain.
Cook carrots and vegetables in steamer or boil until tender, around 8 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs (one at a time).
Sift flour, salt and soda together and mix with nuts.
Mash bananas and add vanilla.
Add flour, nuts and bananas to creamed mixture and blend thoroughly.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine Veg-All, chestnuts, onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle on cheese, then cracker crumbs.
Pour melted oleo over this and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Fold into whipped topping; add pecans and fruit that is well drained.
Pour into 2 graham cracker shells. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: fruit squares
directions: Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and flour.
Mix well and spread on a raised cookie sheet that has been greased and floured.
Score off 24 squares and put a tablespoon of pie filling in the center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, butter and Karo syrup.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Place pecans on top of liquid.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: dressing
directions: Slice celery and onions.

Boil until tender and save liquid. Mix soups, eggs, bread, crackers, margarine and turkey drippings. Mix all together and season with salt, pepper, sage and garlic. Bake at 350 degrees until set and crispy on edges.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients. Fold in oranges. Cover and refrigerate until chilled. Just before serving, fold in bananas and sprinkle with peanuts.

title: tiny ham stuffed tomatoes
directions: Thinly slice tops off tomatoes.
Remove pulp and drain shells on paper towels.
In small bowl, combine deviled ham, sour cream and horseradish.
Fill tomatoes with paste.
Refrigerate.

title: refrigerator sweet pickles
directions: Slice onion in bottom of gallon jar.
Fill with sliced cucumbers.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salt, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Pour over cucumbers and onion and refrigerate for 2 weeks.

title: grape jelly
directions: Soak and wash grapes; remove stems.
Crush grapes and add to water in a Dutch oven, mixing well.
Cover and place over high heat and mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Press mixture through a cheesecloth or strainer, extracting 4 cups juice.
Allow juice to sit overnight in a cool place.
Strain juice through a cheesecloth.
Combine juice and sugar in a large Dutch oven, stirring well.
Place over heat. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to rapid boil.
Add pectin and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and skim off foam with metal spoon.
Pour quickly into hot sterilized jars.
Leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal with layer of paraffin.
Cover with lids.
Yields 4 pints.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Put 3 pats of butter on bottom of dish. Cut potatoes into chunks. Put onion over potatoes. Add rest of butter on top of onion. Cover and cook for 12 minutes on High. Stir them and cook for 7 more minutes.

title: kart-wheels
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, butter, powder sugar, baking powder and just enough milk until dough forms (if dough seems dry, mix in more milk 1 teaspoon at a time).
Divide dough into 6 equal parts.
Shape each part into ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Make an indention 1 3/4-inches in diameter about 3/4-inch deep in center of each flattened ball. Fill each indention with about 2 tablespoons of pie filling.
Bake until edges begin to brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 Kart-Wheels.
Fun for kids to make.

title: "dump" cake
directions: The key word here is "dump."
"Dump" pie filling in ungreased cake pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on pie filling.
"Dump" dry cake mix on top of pie filling.
Cut butter into small squares and place on top of cake mix here and there.
Bake at 375° until top of cake is golden brown.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa; add milk.
Cook on medium heat until boiling.
Boil
for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until melted;
add
vanilla.
Add
oats last, stir until well mixed. Spoon out on waxed paper.

title: 5 in 1 salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Best if made the day before using.

title: almond roca cookies
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients, except chocolate bar and almonds.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
While warm, spread the chocolate bar (melted) over top.
Sprinkle the chopped almonds over.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: lemon dill cheese
directions: Mix all together and store in a tightly covered container. This cheese keeps very well for a week at least, but cannot be frozen.

title: chocolate chess pies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, then butter, vanilla, cream and eggs. Beat together with mixer.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: crispix snack
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over Crispix.
Put all in large bag with powdered sugar and shake.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix in order as given above.
Bake in large, greased baking dish in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown. Do not overcook or the cornbread will be soggy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli in microwave until tender (about 12 minutes).
Drain well.
Combine eggs, soup, mayonnaise, cheese, pepper and broccoli in casserole dish. Sprinkle crackers over top.
Cover and bake for about 30 minutes. Uncover and bake about 10 more minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: microwave chocolate peanut butter clusters
directions: Combine morsels in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High at 100% for 3 to 4 minutes or until melted.
Stir halfway through the cooking.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper. Store in airtight container.
Yields 4 to 4 1/2 dozen.

title: canadian brown bread
directions: Cook oatmeal and let cool.
Add molasses, sugar, shortening, yeast and salt.
Flour to knead.
Let rise.
Pout in loaves and let rise a second time.
Bake at 350°.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Heat oil in 12 x 8-inch dish at High for 2 minutes.
Stir in beef, garlic and ginger; cook at High 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Stir twice.
Add broccoli.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook at High 5 to 6 minutes or until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Stir once.
Blend cornstarch with broth and soy sauce until smooth; stir in beef mixture.
Cook at High 3 to 4 minutes or until sauce is thicker; stir once.
Yields 4 servings.

title: casserole italiano
directions: In skillet, brown and break up the hamburger.
Add onion, garlic and oregano; simmer.
Pour off fat.
Set aside.
In casserole dish, add tomato soup, 2 cups of cheese, salt, water and cooked noodles.
Mix together.
Take hamburger and combine with other ingredients in casserole dish.
Add remaining cup of cheese to the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: raspberry fruit mound
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add 1 cup of cold water.
After this mixture cools, add other ingredients.
Pour into ring mold and let chill.
Remove from mold when firm.

title: jean moore's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll thin.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Cook in 325° oven.
Remove from cookie sheet while warm.

title: fancy green bean casserole
directions: *May substitute cream of mushroom soup and blend half the onions into the bean mixture, placing the other half on top.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain off fat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Halve peppers; remove seeds.
Place peppers in 10 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese; top with meat.
Repeat until all used.
Combine milk, eggs and flour.
Beat until smooth; pour over chilies.
Bake in oven for 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: good ol' chili
directions: Crumble ground beef into slow cooker. Add beans, onion and garlic.
In medium bowl, stir tomatoes with juice, tomato paste, water, chili powder, salt, oregano, cumin and pepper until blended.
Stir into meat mixture. Scrape down sides of slow cooker. Cover and cook on high for 3 1/2 to 4 hours or on low for 7 to 8 hours or until onion is tender.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, then beat in eggs, one at a time. Add remaining ingredients, beating well.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Remove meat from bones and tear into small pieces.
Mix cheese, soup and mayonnaise.
Place layer of chicken in buttered casserole or baking dish.
Add a layer of broccoli.
Pour half the soup mixture over first layer.
Add another layer of the remaining chicken; remaining broccoli and remaining soup mixture.
Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm dressing over this about 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in preheated oven.

title: scrambled cabbage
directions: Heat bacon drippings and oil in large skillet.
Stir in cabbage, celery, onion, green pepper and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with sugar and salt.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes. Stir once or twice during cooking.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine. Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Mix together the yogurt and whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Top with fruit of your choice. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 teaspoons oil.
Combine cream cheese, liquid smoke and oil.
Stir in onions.
Fold in salmon. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: parmesan biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to hot, 450°.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in bowl.
Stir in cheese.
Add butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in enough buttermilk just until dough holds together.
Knead dough slightly on a lightly floured surface.
Pat or roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits with 2-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated hot oven, 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: quick chicken dumpling soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine soup and 2 2/3 cups of milk; bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat. In a bowl, combine biscuit mix with remaining milk just until blended. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto simmering soup. Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes longer or until dumplings test done (do not lift lid while simmering). Yields 4 servings.

title: cream puffs
directions: Boil water.
Add 1/8 teaspoon salt and shortening.
Add flour, stirring until it is not sticky.
Let cool.
Add 4 eggs, 1 at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Place on cookie sheet, about 1 rounded tablespoonful per cream puff.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain. Add onion, tomatoes, ketchup, steak sauce and green peppers. Simmer for 30 minutes. Cook macaroni and drain. Add beef mixture, salt and pepper to taste. Add soup and mix well. Pour in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer all the ingredients, except the mayo and sugar.
Spread the mayo over top, like icing.
Sprinkle sugar over mayo.

title: paprikas krumpli
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add peppers and garlic.
Later, add tomato, paprika and water as much as needed.
Cook until ready, 3/4 to 1 hour, slowly until tender and thick.
Stir once in a while.

title: cole slaw
directions: Toss cabbage, peppers, onion and carrots together.
Mix mayonnaise, Old Bay, vinegar and sugar.
Add to mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: iowa basting sauce for ham
directions: Heat and stir until sugar melts.

title: traditional maryland oyster stew
directions: In 4-quart pan, cook oysters with liquid, over low heat until edges of oysters just begin to curl.
Add milk, margarine or butter, salt and pepper.
Heat slowly until hot; do not boil.
For extra zip, sprinkle seafood seasoning on each serving.
Makes about 6 cups of stew.

title: randy's instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all together and store in a jar.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding according to box.
Layer as follows:
graham crackers, instant vanilla pudding, graham crackers, instant vanilla pudding, graham crackers and chocolate pie filling.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, chopped ham, onions and Worcestershire sauce with mixer.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Butter a cookie sheet or line with wax paper.
Cook sugars and milk over medium heat, stirring until mixture starts to boil.
Add butter, pecans and soda.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until it reaches the soft ball stage (when a bit of candy mixture dropped into cold water forms a soft ball) or 238° on a candy thermometer. Remove from heat and beat with a spoon until mixture is creamy and begins to thicken.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. (If mixture becomes too hard, return to heat and add a little water.)
Makes 24 small pralines.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Place in oven and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave rocky road fudge
directions: Combine chips and peanut butter in a large microwavable bowl. Nuke at 2/3 power for 5 minutes.
Stir until melted and fold in marshmallows and peanuts.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch cake pan and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: oven-roasted sweet potato fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Brush with 1 teaspoon of oil.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/2-inch thick wedges.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add remaining teaspoon of oil, salt and pepper.
Toss.
Spread potatoes in single layer on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until golden and crisp.
Makes 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread and cut into cubes.
Beat eggs and milk; add seasonings.
Lightly butter a 2-quart casserole.
Line bottom with 1/2 of the bread cubes and sprinkle with 1/3 of the cheese.
Repeat cheese and bread layers, then pour milk and egg mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven. Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with parsley.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes more. Serves 8.

title: chicken papagano
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add 1/4 cup dried onion and 2 tablespoons salt.
Cook to debone.
Remove and cool.
Cook noodles in chicken broth until tender; drain.
Rinse in cold water.
When chicken is cool, debone and cut into good-sized pieces.
Combine with noodles and rest of ingredients and toss with dressing. Chill; cut chestnuts into quarters, ripe olives in halves and artichokes into quarters.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Combine milk and eggs and add to flour. Beat well.
Pour into hot drippings in pan, all at once.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
While roast is cooking, chill mixture in refrigerator.

title: penuchi
directions: Put sugar and milk in saucepan and boil, stirring constantly, until syrup reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine but do not stir and set aside to cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla; beat until mixture is thick and creamy.
Stir in nuts. Pour into lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: coconut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine liquid ingredients.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Blend carefully. Let stand 20 minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread(delicious!)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: tahini salad
directions: Chop tomatoes and cucumbers medium fine.
Prepare tahini by mixing it with 2 tablespoons warm water.
Add lemon juice and mix tomatoes with other ingredients.
Garnish with olive oil.
Chopped onions and dried mint are optional.

title: holiday wreath
directions: Combine marshmallows, margarine and vanilla.
Melt slowly on low heat.
Add food coloring after marshmallows are melted.
Stir to blend the coloring.
Remove from heat.
Stir corn flakes until all are green.
Empty corn flakes onto tray covered with waxed paper.
Using your hands, mold the mixture into a circle.
You can use cherries to decorate.

title: quick spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in 4 quarts of boiling water until tender. Drain.
Brown hamburger in skillet.
Mix spaghetti, hamburger and spaghetti sauce together in pan.
Heat until hot.
Top with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Serve with crackers or garlic bread.

title: party cheese fondue
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small heavy saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated and cheese melts.
Transfer to fondue pot; place over heating unit to keep hot.
Serve with breadsticks, apple slices or nacho chips.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Soak bread and rice in milk.
Add remaining ingredients except tomato juice and tomatoes.
Form into balls.
Place in baking pan.
Pour tomato juice and tomatoes over balls.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute rice in oil until golden; add remaining ingredients. Stir well, then cover for 25 minutes or until dry on low heat.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a large greased casserole dish.
Cover with crust (recipe follows).

title: meaty chili with beans
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, celery and garlic in a Dutch oven; cook until beef is browned, stirring to crumble meat. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Yield:
about 8 cups.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Fry meat and seasonings.
Add tomato sauce, hominy and chili powder.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together, and eggs, vanilla extract, almond extract.
Add flour and sugar.
Grease and flour bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2-2 hours.

title: economical pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla to first mixture.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: rice cakes
directions: Use rice cakes as hush puppies or with butter, honey, jam, etc.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Cook chicken until done, in 8 cups of water.
Take chicken out of water.
Add all ingredients except for chicken and rice.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add chicken and rice.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: sausage, peppers and onions
directions: Brown sausage on medium heat lifting from the pan frequently so it doesn't stick.
After browning sausage, add water to sausage to continue cooking.
Remove seeds from green peppers and cut in strips.
Slice onions.
Add both to sausage and continue cooking until sausage is done.
This is a very versatile recipe.
Just increase or decrease the amount of sausage, peppers and onions as you need.

title: knock you nakeds
directions: Combine and mix well cake mix, nuts, 1/3 cup milk and butter. Press half of mixture into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish; bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Melt caramel candy in top of double boiler with 1/2 cup milk (or microwave).
When caramel mixture is well mixed, pour over baked mixture.
Cover with chocolate chips and pour rest of dough on top of chips.
Bake for 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool before slicing.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Rinse and scrub potatoes.
Pat dry.
Prick with a fork.
Bake at 375° until done.
Cut a thin slice off top of each potato. Scoop out pulp.
Put in a bowl.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water for 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup, sour cream, melted oleo and seasoning mixture (from Stove Top dressing).
Butter casserole dish; put 1/2 bread crumbs from Stove Top.
Add squash, onion and carrots.
Spoon on soup mixture; top with rest of bread crumbs.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: gelatin custard
directions: Soften cream cheese for 20 seconds in the microwave. Add the sugar and mix it with a spoon until completely soft. Add the milk and keep mixing, then add the fruit cocktail (with the syrup).

title: banana ginger muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare muffin pan with paper muffin cups.
In medium bowl, combine bananas, maple syrup, orange juice, applesauce, ginger and lemon.
Mix the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together in a large bowl.
Add the banana mixture and mix.
Do not overmix.
Spoon the batter into paper muffin cups, filling each cup about 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.
Cool.
Makes 12 muffins. Calories: 137.
Fat: 0.4 grams.
Fat: 3%.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; drain and squeeze out moisture.
Lay on paper towels to dry.
Mix thawed and dry spinach with remaining ingredients.
Chill for at least two hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: great peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press 5 peanut halves atop each, or crisscross with fork tines.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.

title: snickers pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place pie crust in pie pan.
Bake crust 5 to 7 minutes or until very light brown.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla with a mixer until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup of fruit and mix for 30 seconds.
Pour into pie crust and chill in freezer for 2 hours. Top with remaining fruit and serve chilled.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble and then drain.
Prepare 9-inch pie shell.
Mix
cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in shell. Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Place foil around edges so it will not burn during this time.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Wash, pare and dice eggplant.
Cook in boiling, salted water about 5 minutes.
Drain and place in greased casserole.

title: baked potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes and pat dry.
Quarter each potato.
Cut each quarter crosswise into 1/4-inch slices, cutting to, but not through, bottom of potato to resemble a fan.
Place each potato wedge, skin side down, on large baking sheet.
Set aside.
Combine all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Brush tops and sides of potatoes with mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter until light and fluffy.
Mix in about 1/2 of the cake mix, the egg and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry dressing
directions: Heat to boiling the lemon juice, pineapple juice and sugar. Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks well and add small amount of hot fruit syrup slowly.
Return heated mixture to the hot syrup, beating constantly with wire whip.
Return to low heat and cook until thickened.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream and nutmeg.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In large mixer bowl, stir flour, soda and salt together.
Add remaining ingredients, except candy and mix at medium speed of electric mixer until well combined, scraping bowl occasionally. Chill dough for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in a large pot.
Add onion and cook over low heat to wilt (10 minutes).
Add garlic, celery and carrot.
Cook, stirring, 1 minute longer.
Mix in spices and herbs.
Add bell peppers, beans, tomatoes with juice and vegetable broth.
(I used dried vegetable broth or water.)
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low and cook, partially covered, for 10 minutes.
One-half hour before serving, add zucchini and/or other leftover veggies and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, cover and heat on low heat for 20 minutes only.
Add parsley and serve.
(I added some salsa to taste for an extra zing.)

title: meat ballsfort morgan, colorado
directions: Put meat balls in oven a few minutes, then drain.

title: crabmeat english muffins
directions: Mix everything except muffins.
Spread mixture on muffins. Put under broiler until brown and bubbly.
Cut muffins into 4 pieces and serve.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook peanuts at 325° until done (toasted).
Mix sugar, water and Karo.
Cook mixture, stirring constantly, until it starts to boil.
Let it boil until it reaches 236° on a candy thermometer (or until it forms soft ball in cup of cold water).
Take off heat and add oleo and vanilla.
Beat until it starts to thicken.
Add peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 9 x 13 pan with vegetable oil spray.
Place all ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer on low for 1 minute.
Scrape bowl and mix on medium for 2 minutes.
The batter will look thick and well blended.
Pour into pan, smoothing top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with chocolate glaze.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Place apples (peeled, cored and sliced) into bottom of dish.
Pour sugar over apples.
Pour cranberry sauce over apples.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, nuts and flour.
Pour over cranberries and apples.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 can asparagus juice to soup mixture. Place rice in bottom of dish. Alternate layers of asparagus, soup and cheese. Place pork chops on top with lots of butter.
Cook in oven at 375° for 1 hour or until desired tenderness of chops.
Cover with foil for the first 1/2 hour.
Uncover so chops will brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes. Peel and mash. Add butter, milk and salt. Place in a buttered casserole. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Push marshmallows down into mixture. Bake in a 350° oven until marshmallows are brown, about 15 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: coco lopez coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package instructions in 10 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
While still warm, poke holes in top with fork and pour Eagle Brand milk on top of cake.
Let cool.
After cooling, pour Coco Lopez over cake.
Refrigerate at least overnight.
Ice cake with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top.
Keeps several days in refrigerator, if you can resist!
Serves 12 to 16 easily; it is very rich (and good!).

title: baby carrots with horseradish
directions: Cook carrots in 2 cups water, or steam them over 2 cups water. Use 1/4 cup of the cooking water (drain the rest) and mix with onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Arrange carrots in an ovenproof serving dish.
Top with horseradish sauce, cracker crumbs and dot of butter.
Sprinkle on paprika.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: oven baked potatoes
directions: Thoroughly
wash
potatoes and pat dry.
Slice potatoes in half, lengthwise.
Sprinkle onions across top of 1 half and top with the other half.
Wrap bacon slices around potatoes to hold them together.
Wrap in aluminum foil and place in baking pan. Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: ben's favorite casserole
directions: Boil and drain potatoes.
In a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch casserole dish, place ham in a layer, followed by half of potatoes.
Cover potatoes with cheese slices.
Repeat potato and cheese layers, adding salt and pepper, as desired.
Dot with margarine.
Pour milk over top.
May add more milk, if you like. Bake at 350° until cheese has melted and milk is bubbly.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each one.
Alternate flour and 7-Up. Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then reduce oven to 300° for 35 minutes. Bake in Bundt pan.
Remove from oven and let cool on a rack.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into ball.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken in just enough water to cover chicken.
While chicken is boiling, cook noodles.
When chicken is done, cut up into bite-size pieces or as desired.
Measure out 2 cans of broth and mix it and the cream of mushroom soup together over heat until well mixed.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Place margarine, oats and water in a large bowl; stir well. Cool completely.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let set out of oven for 5 minutes.
Add topping.

title: apple butter(microwave oven)
directions: In 2-quart glass casserole combine apples and cider.
Microwave (High), covered, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes until apples are soft.
Transfer to food mill or blender for smoothing, to even texture.
Return to casserole; combine with sugar, cinnamon, pie spice and cloves.
Microwave (High) 12 to 15 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes until mixture thickens.
Store in freezer or refrigerator in sterilized jars.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, vanilla and milk together.
Bring to a boil and let it boil for a few seconds. Remove from heat and let stand. Cool for about 10 minutes, then add peanut butter and beat until creamy.
Pour in a buttered dish and let cool.

title: easy mexican dish
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet and drain.
Combine the beans, soup and tomatoes and add to the meat mixture.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, place a layer of chips on bottom.
Add mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: crab dip
directions: In a large heavy skillet, melt margarine.
Add softened cream cheese.
Blend well; add garlic powder and stir.
Add crab meat; mix in slowly.
Remove from heat.

title: potato casserole
directions: Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Spread grated cheese on top.

title: norwegian christmas bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Sift cardamon, flour and baking powder together (save out a small amount to mix with raisins and fruit).
Add to mixture, alternating the flour and milk.
Mix raisins and fruits with flour; add to total mixture. Put into 1 large loaf pan or divide between 2 small loaf pans. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bill mcelwain's scallops with lobster sauce
directions: In metal baking dish, melt butter.
Place scallops in butter. Add croutons and mushrooms. Toss to coat evenly.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic powder and pepper. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare the pastry.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in the pastry lined pie pan.
Beat eggs lightly and blend in cream, salt, sugar and pepper.
Pour mixture into pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 425° then reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes later.
Let pie stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: everyday broccoli and cheese chicken
directions: Cook chicken in skillet for 10 minutes or until done.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add broccoli and reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is tender and broccoli is done.
Stir occasionally.
Can be served over linguine noodles.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Heat in microwave for 5 minutes or 10 minutes in a saucepan. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, coconut, corn flakes, nuts, vanilla and salt.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine ingredients (except icing).
Spread into cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour, add milk.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10 - 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Recipe makes 12 muffins.

title: mexican surprise
directions: Spread jalapeno bean dip on plate, then alternate ingredients in layers as listed.
Dip with chips.

title: banana ice cream sandwich
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine pudding and milk.
Mix on low speed of electric mixer until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Chill until set, about 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream or topping. Spread 1/2 cup pudding mixture on 8 crackers.
Top with remaining crackers.
Freeze until firm.

title: congealed coca cola salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries & pineapple into sauce pot. Add 1/4 cup water. Cook with Jell-o until it comes to a boil. Cool. Add cream cheese & beat. Add other ingredients. Refrigerate until congealed.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add to other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes in 300° oven.

title: crock-pot carolina barbecue
directions: Trim fat from roast and place in a 5-quart electric slow cooker. Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and crushed red pepper. Add sugar and vinegar. Cook on low 12 to 14 hours. To reduce cooking time, follow slow cooker directions for cooking on high. When done, remove roast from cooker and place in a large skillet, reserving cooking juices. Flake or shred roast, removing any fat or gristle. Mix meat, some of the cooking juices and ketchup. Simmer mixture over medium heat until juices evaporate. Serve on lightly toasted hamburger buns. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Blend butter, cheese and flour.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix well using hands.
Roll into small balls and flatten on cookie sheet. Cook 15 to 20 minutes on 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt margarine; cook next 3 ingredients until tender.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Mix all together with chicken and spaghetti. Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add chicken broth, if needed.

title: coconut-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to first mixture and mix thoroughly.
Fold in oats, coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
(Suitable for freezing.)
Makes 9 dozen cookies.

title: betty's casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion in skillet.
Combine all other ingredients, except tortillas and cheese in a large saucepan. Cook until blended and smooth.
Add cooked meat and onion to saucepan.
Either fry or bake tortillas until crisp.
In a casserole, layer meat mixture and tortillas.
Top with cheese. Bake at 325° for about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lazy pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart round baking dish.
Empty can of pie filling in center (do not stir) and dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 40 minutes or until golden color on top.

title: yummy chicken
directions: In large pot, melt butter, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, basting on all sides with butter mixture.
Cover with lid and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take out and add mushrooms.
Bake until mushrooms are cooked (about 15 minutes).
Put onion rings over top and then grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until the cheese melts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender. Mash potatoes, adding sugar and spice to taste. When potato mixture is cool enough to handle, take a large marshmallow and with potato mixture form a ball. Dip in melted margarine and roll in graham cracker crumbs. Bake in baking dish greased with margarine. Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes, or until potato balls will begin to crack and you can see the marshmallow melting.

title: yummy eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant, covered in water, until tender; drain and mash. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until creamy.
Sift flour and baking powder. Add to eggs and sugar. Bring to boiling point the milk and butter. Add this mixture plus the vanilla to above and pour into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add pumpkin and stir in dry ingredients; add nuts.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, Karo syrup and salt.
Add well beaten eggs and stir in nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in raw pastry shell for 1 hour at 300°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well. Chill. Serve with fruit of your choice.

title: braised leg of lamb
directions: Insert slivers of garlic in top side of lamb.
In heavy Dutch oven in vegetable oil, lightly brown meat.
Remove lamb from pot. Add chopped vegetables, cover pot and simmer vegetables for 10 minutes.
Return lamb to Dutch oven, add broth and wine.
Bring to a boil.
Cover pot and place in 325° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until lamb is tender.
Remove lamb from Dutch oven.
Pour broth through sieve and press vegetables to get as much puree as possible.
Remove fat by skimming or pouring over ice cubes. Measure broth.
Thicken broth by using 1 tablespoon cornstarch for each cup of broth.
Carve meat and serve with gravy.
Number of servings will depend on weight of lamb.

title: spaghetti ham salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and run cold water over spaghetti.
Mix dressing and salad seasoning together.
Put spaghetti in big bowl and pour dressing over. Marinate overnight.

title: spaghetti crescent casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in sauce mix and spaghetti sauce; heat until hot and bubbly.
Combine Mozzarella cheese and sour cream.
Spread spaghetti into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour meat mixture over spaghetti.
Spoon cheese mixture over meat.
Separate crust dough into two rectangles and place over cheese mixture.
Combine Parmesan cheese and margarine. Crumble evenly over the dough.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Bread crumbs, buttered, can be substituted for the rolls.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Hollow out tomatoes.
Turn upside down for a few minutes to drain.
Chop tomato pulp.
Add other ingredients to make a thick filling.
Fill tomatoes and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf substitute
directions: Mix well. Place in loaf pan and steam 1 hour. Brown in oven.

title: texas barbecue
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Roast, covered, 4 hours at 275°.
Cool and pull apart.
Combine 1 medium onion (chopped with the meat). Bring last 8 ingredients to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes. Pour over meat and onion mixture.
Serve on warm buttered hamburger buns.

title: connie's coffee cake
directions: Cream together the flour, oil, sugar and brown sugar until dry and crumbly and looks like pie crust.
Take out 1 1/2 cups of dry mix and add cinnamon and chopped nuts.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Beat together until well blended.
Pour into well-greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: banana nut chip cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar and then add the beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter and cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and peanut butter with
electric beater. Add sugar and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in pie shell and chill.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Crush garlic and blend with cooking oil, salt, ground pepper, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, chopped parsley and hot pepper sauce.
Use a blender if you have one.
Rinse 3 pounds of shelled, deveined, large uncooked shrimp.
Drain and arrange on 8 skewers.
Set the skewers over a baking pan.
Brush shrimp with the sauce.
Cover with Saran Wrap and allow to stand overnight or at least 4 hours in the refrigerator.
When ready to use, broil for 10 minutes, turning frequently and brushing with the marinade when you do.
Serve on freshly cooked rice.
Garnish with chicory and tiny skewers of orange sections, olives and pickles.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mellow fudge squares
directions: Mix melted butter and cocoa and set aside.
Beat eggs. Gradually add sugar and salt.
Fold flour into egg mixture.
Next fold in cocoa and butter mixture above, the vanilla and chopped pecans.
Bake in greased, floured, large, oblong cake pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediate cut large marshmallows in half and place, cut side down, on cake.
Return to oven (5 minutes) until melted.
Let cool.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Place graham crackers on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 2 boxes of pudding and 3 1/2 cups milk for 2 minutes.
Fold in Birds-Eye Cool Whip.
Gradually layer pudding mixture and graham crackers, ending with graham crackers on top.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix ingredients and cook to a soft ball stage.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine, a drop of red food coloring and 1 3/4 cups powdered sugar.
Beat well and drop by spoonful on foil.

title: aunt matt's punch
directions: Mix jello with water as directed on package. Add all juices and mix well. Chill in refrigerator.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown meats in hot fat. Add soy sauce and 1 cup water. Simmer 2 minutes. Add celery and onions. Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Blend cornstarch and water. Stir into meat mixture. Add chestnuts, bean sprouts and mushrooms. Heat through. Season. Serve over rice or chow-mein noodles. Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Mix zucchini, onions and bell pepper.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 1 hour, then drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and heat to boiling.
Boil 2 or 3 minutes.
Add squash to mixture, then bring to boil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening until light, scraping sides of bowl often.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, beating until smooth and fluffy after each addition.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Add flour mixture and mashed banana alternately to creamed mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Gently fold in chopped nuts.
Turn into lightly greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan; cool on wire rack.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix and chill for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Follow steps on package for softer rice.
Brown hamburger. Cook rice; mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oreos 'n cream
directions: Crumble half of the Oreos onto bottom of 2-quart dish.
Mix pudding with milk as directed, then add cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix well, then pour mixture onto crumbled Oreos in dish.
Crumble remaining Oreos on top. Chill.
Delicious!

title: monte cristo sandwiches
directions: Beat milk and eggs together in small bowl.
In a skillet, melt butter (about 2 tablespoons) until hot.
Dip one side of bread into milk-egg mixture.
Place in hot pan; add layer of ham, slice cheese, layer of turkey and slice of cheese; dip another slice of bread into milk-egg mixture.
Place on top with dipped side up. Take spatula to bottom.
Cook until brown.
Carefully flip sandwich over to brown other side.
Remove; add a pat of butter to the top.
Delicious with syrup over the top.
Looks like you just made a French toast sandwich.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes.
Add other ingredients.
Stir well.
Cook by spoonfuls in heavy skillet (iron) until brown.
Use olive oil or vegetable oil.

title: italian delight
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Combine the hamburger and noodles along with the remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat until warm.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a strip of bacon.
Cover the bottom of an 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish with the dried beef. Place breast on top of the dried beef.
Mix the soup and the sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 325°.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated milk, butter, Marshmallow Fluff and salt in a quart saucepan.
Stir over low heat until blended.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat, being careful not to mistake escaping air bubbles for boiling.
Boil slowly, stirring constantly for 5 minutes to soft-ball stage.

title: hillary's chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder on waxed paper.
Beat together shortening, sugars and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer until creamy. Add eggs, beating until light and fluffy.
Gradually add remaining dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: mom's rhubarb custard pie
directions: Blend
and mix well the eggs, sugar and flour.
Stir in the rhubarb.
Pour into a prepared unbaked pie shell and cover with
a lattice top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream, nonfat frozen yogurt or whipped cream.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the corn and set aside in large roasting pan.
Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour hot caramel over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into two shallow roasting pans.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove from oven.
Pour into bowl; toss and stir while cooling. Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 5 quarts caramel popped corn.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Combine chicken, soups, sour cream and almonds.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt butter and crush Ritz crackers.
Combine butter, cracker crumbs and poppy seed.
Spread cracker mixture over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles, approximately 45 minutes.

title: summer squash bake
directions: Wash and cut up the squash.
Dice the onion and add to squash. Cook all in boiling salted water.
Drain and mash with potato masher.
Add about 3 tablespoons butter with salt and pepper to taste.
Beat eggs.
Stir a little hot squash into eggs before gradually adding eggs to squash.
Mix in flour, milk and last 2 tablespoons butter.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: 1. In a large non stick skillet, saute onion and garlic in 1/4 c. chicken broth until cooked.
2. Add can of Ro-Tel tomatoes, pureed tomatoes, chicken
broth, green chilies, chili powder, Mexican seasoning,
and cumin. Add chicken and heat to boiling, reduce heat
and simmer 20-30 minutes.
3. Meanwhile cut tortillas into thin strips and add to
soup mixture. Simmer 15 more minutes.
4. Garnish with cheese and sour cream.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix together in saucepan the flour, butter, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Let cool.
Add to the cool sauce mashed up salmon, onion, egg, celery and bell pepper.
Stir until well mixed.
Add cracker crumbs to make stiff.
Make heaping tablespoonfuls of salmon mixture into balls.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Drop into hot oil until brown.

title: french onion soup - dannenberg style
directions: Brown onion in frying pan.
Then add green peppers to saute. Put mix in quart size pan.
Put cold water into pan; heat to boil. (Add small noodles, if desired.)
Add 2 beef bouillon cubes or more for flavor.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Use a 3-quart ovenproof casserole pan.
Press hamburger into bottom of pan.
Stand Tater Tots up on meat (cover entire top). Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
If using microwave, microwave at High for 30 minutes.
Stop during baking to turn several times so it cooks evenly.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine broth and 1 can of chilies in a large skillet; bring to a boil. Add chicken; reduce heat, and simmer 15 minutes or until chicken is done, turning chicken once. Remove chicken from cooking liquid, reserving cooking liquid; cool chicken. Shred meat with two forks, and set aside.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Bring 8 cups hot water to boiling.
Add pasta.
Reduce heat. Cook in gently boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Return to pan.
Halve pepperoni; add to pasta.
Stir in pizza sauce, 3/4 cup Mozzarella cheese, mushrooms, olives and Parmesan.
Transfer to a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 15 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken for 1 hour. Take off the bones and put in the bottom of baking dish. Add soup to this. Pour Stove Top on top of the soup and chicken. Bake at 300°, covered, for 45 minutes, then bake 109 to 15 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: layered pudding delight
directions: Mix pudding; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir together with Cool Whip.
Layer together in serving bowl with graham crackers.
Make top layer graham crackers and top with cherry pie filling.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: texas hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and bell pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off grease.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and black pepper; heat through.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: raisin carrot muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients with carrots, raisins and pineapple. Mix in remaining ingredients and spoon into cups.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Cook all ingredients in pan until brown.
Add the chicken and mushroom soups.
Just before serving, add the sour cream.

title: norma's apple squares
directions: Mix flour and salt. Cut in shortening until crumbly. Add water and lightly mix until blended.
Divide in half. Roll out half of the dough and place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Trim sides to halfway up the pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix seasoning packet from stuffing mix with melted butter. In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine
packet of bread crumbs from stuffing mix with corn, milk and egg.
Stir in seasoning mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; arrange in buttered shallow dish or pan.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, sour cream, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter; stir in crumbs and cheese.
Top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rum coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in large tube pan at 300°.
Spray pan with Pam.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet for 15 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Add catsup, cheese, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Simmer until most of liquid has evaporated.
Serve on buns.
