title: monkey cake
directions: Take biscuits and cut into quarters.
Put sugar and cinnamon in a bag.
Put biscuits in the bag and shake.
Place biscuits in a greased tube pan (layered).

title: old-fashion "pull" candy(old family recipe)
directions: Cook syrup in heavy skillet.
(If using a candy thermometer, boil at 260° for about 20 to 25 minutes).
Test by dropping some from a spoon in cool water.
It will string and bead on bottom like sticks.
If a string of the syrup tinkles or clicks on glass, it is ready.
Pour syrup on buttered surface.
Turn outer edges in until cool enough to handle.
Grease your hands well with butter and pull until it turns almost white.
Make it into rope-like sections and roll them in the chopped peanuts.
Let cool.
Cut into 2 to 3-inch pieces.

title: grandma's oatmeal bread
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over first 5 ingredients and stir. Cool until lukewarm.
Dissolve 1 tablespoon dry yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add to batter:
add flour until thick enough (about 5 cups).
Place in greased bowl.
Cover with towel.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again in loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and bell pepper until browned, then add other ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Combine dressing, onion and pepper; heat.
Tear spinach in bite size pieces into salad bowl.
Add crumbled bacon and cheese. Toss with dressing.
Top with egg.
Serves 6.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients add a small amount of water and simmer about 40 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: corny snack mix
directions: In large bowl mix popcorn, corn pops cereal and corn chips. Melt white chips.
Pour over mixture "mix".
Spread onto wax paper, cool.
Store in airtight container.
Very good!

title: spaghetti
directions: Bring water to boil.
Make hamburger balls and put in water. When meat is done, add spaghetti, onion, garlic salt, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
When spaghetti is done, add Velveeta cheese and let melt, then ready to eat.

title: warm gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan.
Mix together the flour, baking soda, ginger and cinnamon.
With electric mixer, beat butter and brown sugar at high speed until pale brown and creamy. Break the eggs into butter mixture and beat until completely blended.
Add half the flour mixture and mix at low speed.
Add sour cream and mix. Add remaining flour and mix. Add molasses and mix until smooth.
Fill prepared pan and bake about 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain juice from asparagus.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, alternate layer of asparagus, eggs, almonds and soup.
Pour remaining soup over top of casserole and sprinkle with cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix all the ingredients together and let simmer 20 minutes.

title: best ever biscuits
directions: Sift flour and sugar into mixing bowl. Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Blend in milk, roll dough 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut into biscuits.
Place on baking sheet. Brush top with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Place chicken in nonstick skillet and add lemon juice.
Season with garlic powder, pepper, parsley and onion powder.
Cook chicken over high heat, uncovered, turning occasionally.
Serve garnished with parsley sprigs.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: All cans of beans should be 16 ounce size.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onions and celery in a small amount of margarine.
Add broccoli.
Add soup, milk, rice and Cheez Whiz.
Stir and bake in lightly greased casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Mash bananas and add the nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Slice eggplant; leave skin on.
Put eggplant in a pan; sprinkle with salt and cover with water (it takes out the bitterness).

title: snitzel beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Add sugar and vinegar to drippings.
After onion has been sauteed, pour over beans and simmer for 20 minutes.
Crumble in bacon.
Set aside.
Reheat when ready to serve.

title: chicken-turkey casserole
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine hash brown potatoes, sour cream, onions and cheese all together.
Place in baking dish.
Melt butter or margarine.
Crush corn flakes fine and mix with butter. Spread over top of potatoes and bake for about 1 hour.
Serve and enjoy.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Make meatballs and brown.
Add to spaghetti sauce or serve on the side.
Serves 6 (2 each).

title: homemade sherbet
directions: Mix. Put in ice cream freezer.

title: olive surprises
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Add other ingredients.
Chill about 20 minutes.
Shape dough around each olive.
Bake at 400° until done.
Good hot or cold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix sugar, cake flour and salt thoroughly.
Add Crisco and mix on low.
Add 2/3 cup sweet milk; mix on low until creamy.
Add 1/3 cup milk and egg whites, one at a time.
Beat until blended.
Add vanilla.
Place in 2 lined, greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: banana fruit punch
directions: Mix ingredients with 1 gallon of water.
Better if let set overnight.

title: surprise meringues
directions: Beat egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, gradually beating until peaks are stiff. Fold in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Cover cookie sheet with plain paper sack.
Drop mixture on paper by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and freeze in molds.
Will keep frozen for months.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Fold pudding into Cool Whip, then add well-drained fruit cocktail (fresh).

title: easy sauerbraten
directions: Saute meat and onion. Cover with Italian dressing, water and broth. Simmer 3 to 4 hours or cook in crock-pot on low all day. Thicken sauce to gravy consistency with cornstarch and small amount of water.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt together.
Add to shortening, sugar and eggs, then add buttermilk and apples.

title: golden shepherd's pie
directions: Combine ground round, onion, carrot and green pepper in a large, nonstick skillet.
Cook over medium-high heat until beef is browned, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe drippings from skillet with paper towel.
Return beef mixture to skillet; add peas and next 8 ingredients, stirring well.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon beef mixture into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Spread Potato Topping over beef mixture; lightly coat top with cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 15 minutes.
Broil 5 1/2 inches from heat (with electric oven door partially opened) 1 to 2 minutes or until golden.
Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings (296 calories per serving).

title: helen's chocolate cake
directions: Heat milk, butter and chocolate until butter and chocolate are melted.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add melted chocolate mixture to dry ingredients, then add egg and vanilla.
Blend well. Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan, or loaf pan, at 280° for 1 hour.

title: beef & macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni; drain.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add flour, seasonings, and milk; cook 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese; heat until melted.
Add macaroni and dried beef.
Heat 5 minutes.
Pour into casserole.
Melt remaining margarine; toss with bread crumbs. Top casserole with bread crumbs; broil until lightly browned.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve warm or cold with Melba toast or tortilla chips.

title: arizona mountain soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Combine beans with 3 cups water.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Let stand or cover and let stand overnight.
Drain; add 5 1/2 cups fresh water to beans. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, paprika and pepper.
Stir into beans.
Bring to boiling.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour or until rice and beans are done, stirring occasionally. Will be thick.
Makes 8 servings.
Great for Lent.

title: crock-pot barbecue beef
directions: Add all ingredients to crock-pot and cook for 10 hours on low. Uncover for last hour to thicken.
Shred beef and serve over buns. Freezes well.

title: hanky panky's
directions: Brown together the ground chuck and sausage, continuously breaking into small pieces.
Drain grease from the meat.
Cut up Velveeta into chunks; melt together with meat.
Add garlic salt and oregano to mixture.
Serve warm on garlic rounds or miniature bread.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking casserole dish (9 x 13-inch). Place Swiss cheese on top of chicken.
Pour mixture of soup and wine on top of cheese.
Sprinkle top with stuffing mix and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple - walnut bread(lo-cal)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with orange juice.
Beat after each addition.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Pour in two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Contains 120 calories per 1/2 slice.

title: sam's hot dogs
directions: Cook.
Put hot dogs in and simmer until hot dogs are cooked. Serve warm with drinks.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Layer baking sheet with graham crackers.
Melt butter and margarine.
Pour butter mixture and sugar on the graham crackers. Sprinkle nuts on top and bake for 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: hog maw(pig stomach)
directions: Dice enough raw potatoes so that when mixed with sausage and onion they will fill the stomach firmly.
Salt and pepper filling to taste.
Fill the stomach and sew all openings shut.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 3 1/2 hours.
If cooked faster, the stomach might burst.
About half an hour before serving, remove cover and any grease, and brown both sides.
Slice to serve.

title: quick vegetable salad
directions: Chop lettuce in salad bowl.
Then chop onion over lettuce. Spread English peas over onion.
Cover peas with mayonnaise and sprinkle with plenty of Parmesan cheese.
Stand cucumber slices around edge of bowl.
Let chill.

title: best oven-roasted ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix next 2 ingredients.
Brush both sides of 4 slabs of baby-back ribs or 3 slabs of pork spare ribs with mustard then sprinkle with dry rub. Place on upper-middle oven rack.
Place pan under ribs to catch drippings.
Roast 2 to 3 hours for spare ribs, 1/2 to 2 hours for baby-back ribs.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Stir in walnuts and cranberries.
Combine eggs, orange juice, water and oil.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until moist.
Pat into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans.
In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently or beat vigorously 300 strokes by hand. (Batter will be very thick.)
With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into pans.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove; cool.
Fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix flour, salt, dry mustard and egg yolk together.
Stir in vinegar, then add milk.
After cooked and cooled, beat up 1 egg white and fold in.

title: old-fashioned soft sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter to consistency of mayonnaise; add sugar gradually while continuing to cream.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla; beat until light and fluffy. Measure and sift flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
For 3-inch cookies, drop by heaping teaspoons on well-greased cookie sheets well apart.
With spatula, flatten into circles about 2-inches in diameter.
For super size 5-inch cookies, use 1/4 cup measure of batter for each cookie. Flatten into circles 4-inches in diameter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 30 (3-inch) cookies or 18 (5-inch) cookies.

title: chex buddy mix
directions: Microwave on High chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo for 1 minute.
Stir and add vanilla and cereal.
Place 1 1/4 cups powdered sugar in paper grocery bag.
Add mixture; shake.
Place on waxed paper.

title: patty's salad
directions: Blend and beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a bread pan and freeze.
Slice to serve.

title: sooner cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
Cool, then crumble.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: perfect spice cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Put into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until center is done.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Let dates set 2 to 3 minutes in 1 cup boiling water and drain. Shape into balls; let set in refrigerator.
Roll in coconut or melt 1 stick of wax and 1 package chocolate bits and dip them.

title: spinach and artichoke appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake until hot and bubbly, about 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve on crackers or bread, or with cut up fresh vegetables.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush cookie sand mix with soft ice cream.
Pour into an 11 x 13-inch dish and freeze.

title: german chocolate cake(1993 dairy festival 1st place)
directions: Grease and lightly flour two 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans; set aside.
In a saucepan, heat chocolate and water until chocolate melts; cool.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt. In a mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine on medium speed of electric mixer about 30 seconds.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating on medium speed for 1 minute after each.
Beat in chocolate mixture.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately to beaten mixture, beating after each addition.
Fold in egg whites.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water.
Let this set until it begins to thicken.
Add mashed bananas, pineapple and frozen strawberries.
Pour half of this mixture into a large mold rubbed with mayonnaise.
Spread sour cream and let set for a few minutes, then pour the other half of the Jell-O on top of the sour cream.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Refrigerate overnight, if possible.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Blend in applesauce, raisins and pecans.
Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, allspice, cocoa and soda; add to cream mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Frost with frozen coconut and a white frosting.

title: glazed fruit dessert
directions: In a bowl, combine pudding and pineapple juice.
Stir until thickened.
Fold in pineapple, oranges and bananas.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Garnish with whipped topping.
Serves 6.

title: prepared mustard
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add vinegar.
Make a paste.
Add rest of the vinegar and cook.
If too thick, add a little more vinegar and water to taste.
This can be doubled if needed.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients by mixer for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend by mixer for 2 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved. Arrange rolls in Bundt pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch pudding (not instant). Pour melted mixture over rolls. Cover tightly with foil. Let stand overnight on counter. Bake in morning at 350° for 30 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: jalapeno salsa
directions: Combine ingredients and mix them up.
That's it!
If it's not hot enough, add more jalapenos.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients, then stir in everything else. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: In a large cast iron skillet, brown ground beef.
Add onion and Ranch Style beans.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes over low fire. Place a handful of tortilla chips on a plate.
Top with meat and bean mixture, then cheese and then all of the rest.
Be creative. Make it like you like it!

title: praline pecan cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix and butter at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture in bottom and 1 1/2-inches up sides of ungreased 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
If necessary, use floured fingers to press dough in pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in food processor.
Chill and serve.

title: norwegian fish balls
directions: Grind fish several times and add a little milk slowly.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat until light and smooth, then add salt, nutmeg and cornstarch.
Work good together.
Make into small balls, either fry in butter or boil in water.

title: apple anytime cake
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, egg, milk and chopped nuts together.
Fold in pie filling (any kind).
Grease and flour an 8 x 12 pan.
Spread mix evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and bake in pie shell till center is set.
Cook 45 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: black-eyed pea supper
directions: Brown sausage. Drain. In large skillet, combine sausage, green pepper, onion and garlic. Cook 5 minutes. Add tomatoes and seasonings. Pour in black-eyed peas including liquid. Cover and simmer slowly for 20 minutes. Serve with grated cheese on top.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Take off stove; blend in the rest of the ingredients.
Pour in baking dish to cool and then cut in squares.

title: golden ham slice
directions: Place ham slices on rack in an open roasting pan.
Bake in slow oven (325°) 15 minutes.
Drain pineapple, reserving liquid. Combine cornstarch, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add reserved liquid and cook, stirring constantly until thickened and clear.
Stir in pineapple and carrot.
Spread mixture over ham slice and continue baking for 15 to 30 minutes longer.

title: people puppy food
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter in microwave. Mix in cereal and sugar.
Put 10x sugar on at once.
Cereal will separate.

title: calypso beef salad(serves 4)
directions: Combine the yogurt, mayonnaise and ginger.
Cover and refrigerate. Cut the asparagus into 1-inch strips.
Cut the oranges into 1/2-inch slices and then into quarters.
Separate the onion slices into rings and combine with asparagus.

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery.
Mix together all ingredients, saving a few noodles to spread on top.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: english rocks
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour batter over nuts and fruit and mix thoroughly.
Drop from teaspoon on baking sheet and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
These keep well and can be frozen.
Makes a lot but are delicious.

title: mandarin pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crusts. Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: downtown fudge pie
directions: Over low heat, melt butter and chocolate.
Set aside.
Beat eggs until light. To eggs, add syrup, sugar, salt and vanilla. Now add slightly cooled chocolate mixture.
Mix and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Don't overbake!
Pie should shake like custard, so it won't be stiff when cooled. Delicious served warm with vanilla ice cream.
Tastes like a hot fudge sundae.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into small greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scoutmaster's stew
directions: Utensils:
1 large pot, 1 long spoon, 2 to 3 sharp knives, 1 tripod, 1 easy chair, firewood, matches, 2 to 3 Assistant Scoutmasters, 1 rope with hook and 1 skillet.

title: meatball stew
directions: Place the potatoes, carrots, onion, celery and meatballs in a 5-quart slow cooker. In a bowl, combine the remaining ingredients. Pour over meatball mixture. Cover and cook on low 9 to 10 hours or until the vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: cole slaw
directions: Alternate cabbage, onion and green pepper in layers in a bowl with tight fitting lid.
Cover top of ingredients with 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon sugar, salt and vinegar.
Mix together vegetable oil, celery seed and dry mustard seed.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage immediately.
Cover with lid and let set, usually about 4 hours or overnight.
Keeps for weeks in the refrigerator.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You will also need 1 large glass punch bowl.

title: california chicken
directions: Take Cheez-Its crackers and grind into crumbs.
(Use grinder, food processor or mallet and bag for crackers.) Needs to be fine. Take chicken breasts and pound as flat as possible.
Dip chicken in sour cream mixed with seasoned salt, then roll in Cheez-It crumbs.
Then take chicken and roll it up.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: roast beef and gravy
directions: Rinse meat and tenderize both sides.
Put in crock-pot and add onion soup mix and cup of water over that.
Add all the soups. Cook on low in crock-pot for 8 hours or in oven at 350° for 2 hours.
Best served with rice.

title: marinated salad
directions: Combine Greek seasoning and paprika with oils and vinegar in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Add mushrooms and marinate for several hours.
Add onion, tomatoes, avocado, celery and parsley.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Add olives.
Serve in bowls lined with lettuce leaves.
Serves 4.

title: snow cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour 3 (8-inch) cake pans; set aside. Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Blend until moistened; beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Spread batter evenly in three prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool on wire racks.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Cream the shortening with the sugar and add egg.
Alternately mix the sifted mixture and the applesauce and chocolate chips with the cream mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greasing entire pan.
Mix together all the ingredients. Pour into pan, mixing margarine into batter.
Bake for 45 minutes until brown on top and crusty at edges.

title: hodie podie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with cornbread and salad.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Cook seasonings until transparent.
Mix cornstarch and milk together and add to seasonings, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add crabmeat and season.
Mix cornflake crumbs and mayonnaise together and mix with crabmeat mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Slowly sift in confectioners sugar.
Stir in vanilla and lemon juice.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix flour, meal, sugar, mustard and onion together.
Combine egg and milk; mix with dry ingredients.
Roll hot dogs in the dough mixture; fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: fried rice
directions: Chill rice in refrigerator.
In Farberware electric wok, add 1 tablespoon of oil.
Set heat control dial at 200°.
When light goes out, add egg and scramble.
Remove and set aside.
Turn heat control dial to 250° and add remaining oil, onions and garlic. Stir-fry about 1 minute.
Stir in shrimp and water chestnuts; cook cold rice and soy sauce until well mixed, then stir in peas, carrot and egg.
Stir constantly until hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain off fat. Add garlic, bay leaf, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste. Add tomato juice to make consistency of spaghetti. Simmer one hour, uncovered. Remove bay leaf and garlic. Cook noodles.

title: easy gingerbread
directions: Melt shortening and set aside to cool. Beat eggs and set aside. Sift all dry ingredients together. Mix brown sugar, shortening, eggs and molasses. Mix with dry ingredients. Add buttermilk. Mix well and pour into an 8 x 8 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dieter's delight ambrosia
directions: Blend cottage cheese with wire whisk.
Sprinkle dry orange gelatin over mixture.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Fold together. Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Add gelatin to water, set aside.
Put yolks in double boiler, stir in 1/3 c. sugar, lemon rind and juice.
Cook, stirring over boiling water 5 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in gelatin until melted.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites and salt until they form peaks.
Slowly add 1/2 c. sugar, while beating stiff. Gently fold in hot mixture.
Turn into shell, chill.
Can be served with whipped cream.

title: crawfish patties
directions: Grind all vegetables with crawfish tails in food processor. Add eggs, salt and pepper to taste.
Add bread crumbs and mix well. Form into patties, then drench in flour (I prefer flour) or fish fry.
Deep fry until brown.
Serves about 10.

title: beef and rice
directions: Make rice.
Brown meat until done.
Mix with rice and simmer to mix the flavor.
Put grated cheese over top of rice and steak. Serves 4.

title: mama's cherry salad with coke
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to a hard boil.
Pour over jello, stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple and juice.
Allow to cool and add Coke.
Pour into a large mold and chill overnight. Serves 10 to 12.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
In mixing bowl, cream the Crisco and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, beating after each one.
Blend remaining ingredients alternately, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Pour batter in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake for approximately 1 hour.
Cool on wire rack.
Remove from pan.

title: chop suey
directions: Saute pork and shrimp until browned.
Add garlic and onion. Fold in vegetables (except cabbage) and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cabbage; cook 5 more minutes.
Serve.

title: ravioli-broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ravioli with sour cream.
Cut thawed broccoli lengthwise. Put a layer of spears on bottom of dish.
Pour ravioli mixture on top.
Garnish with reserved broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.

title: five flavors cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour. Add extracts in milk.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch round tube pan for 25 minutes at 275°.
Raise temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes more.
Let cool in pan.
Remove and punch holes in cake with toothpick.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Saute onions in 4 tablespoons butter. Add flour and water. When thick, add Cheez Whiz. Combine cheese sauce, broccoli and eggs.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate and top with buttered Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: deviled egg and ham salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine ham, green pepper, onion, mayonnaise, red pepper, vinegar and mustard. Mix until well blended. Set aside. Separate hard cooked egg yolk from whites. Place yolks in small bowl. Mash and stir into ham mixture. Chop egg whites and stir into ham mixture. Let stand 10 minutes to blend flavors. Line 4 plates with lettuce. Arrange tomatoes in fan shape around edge of
lettuce. Spoon salad mixture onto lettuce. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush chicken with 2 tablespoons dressing.
Place
chicken
pieces
in flat pan skin side down; cover with	remaining dressing and sprinkle with spices.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn
chicken; add mushrooms, cheese and paprika. Bake another 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut brittle(microwave oven)
directions: Measure peanuts,
sugar,
syrup
and
salt into a 1 1/2 quart glass
bowl.
Stir
to
blend.
Microwave
minutes, stopping and
stirring
several
times.
(I use a wooden spoon and leave in the dish.) Add oleo and vanilla and microwave an additional 2 minutes without stirring.
Remove candy from oven and add soda. Pour candy onto a buttered cookie sheet and let cool.
As candy cools,
run
a
knife
around outer edges for easier removal from cookie sheet.
Break in pieces.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Pour in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cajun rush's chargrilled shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp, except for final tail section (provides a handle for eating).
Mix all other ingredients in a flat casserole or baking dish and marinate shrimp in resulting sauce for a few minutes.
When chargrill is good and hot, place shrimp on grill. Watch carefully, shrimp cook quickly (2 to 3 minutes).
Turn shrimp after a minute or so and baste with marinade.
Remove from grill as soon as they lose their translucency and turn whitish. Don't overcook! Baste again and serve immediately.
Shrimp should be juicy and full of flavor.

title: grilled potato wedges
directions: Heat grill. In a bowl, combine all above ingredients and mix until well coated. Place on grill and turn over every 7 minutes. Move to center of grill each turn. Grill for 20 minutes of until tender with knife.

title: salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add 1/2 of salad seasoning and 1/2 of salad dressing.
Chill.
Before serving, add the rest of seasoning and salad dressing.
Toss and serve.

title: panned corned beef and cabbage
directions: Melt fat in a frypan. Add the cabbage and corned beef.
Cover tightly.
Cook until cabbage is tender, 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, to prevent sticking.

title: herbed cheese bread
directions: Cut bread into slices (not all the way through).
Put one slice Swiss or Jack cheese between each slice.
Spread with butter mix.
Put in foil boat.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Remove sausage from casing and brown in skillet.
Drain fat from
sausage
and add shredded cheese over sausage.
Mix other ingredients
together
and then add sausage mixture and mix
well. Roll
into
balls	and
place
on ungreased cookie sheet.	Bake for approximately 15 minutes in 350° oven.	Makes around 75.

title: ruth's squash pickles
directions: Place squash, onions and peppers in large container with 1/2 cup salt.
Cover with water and ice cubes.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Mix other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Drain squash mixture and rinse.
Pour liquid mixture over squash and boil for 7 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes 7 pints.

title: cheesy hamburger hash
directions: Cook beef in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until brown; drain. Remove beef and drippings from skillet. Melt butter in same skillet. Add potatoes. Cover and cook over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until tender. Stir in beef, tomatoes and seasoning. Cook, stirring occasionally, until thoroughly heated. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley. Cover and heat until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and bake, uncovered, in buttered dish at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: collard greens
directions: Place water, red pepper and meat in large pot and boil for 1 hour.
Prepare greens by discarding damaged or yellowed leaves. Cut away tough stems from each leaf.
Wash greens individually until water runs clear and free of dirt and grit.
Collard greens are large and usually require cutting before cooking.
To do so, fold leaf in half at its center vein, fold over once or twice, then cut in half with scissors or a knife.
Add remaining ingredients to meat in boiling water and then the greens.
Cover and cook rapidly for about 30 minutes or until greens are tender yet firm.
Serve with diced raw onions and vinegar.
Yields 16 servings.

title: ice cream cake roll
directions: Bake on cookie sheet at 375° until done.
Don't overbake. Turn out on towel covered with powdered sugar and roll.
Cool, then unroll and add ice cream.
Reroll and freeze.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar together.
Press that into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 250°.
Let that cool.
Soften and mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread over crumb mixture and set aside.
Mix jello in 2 cups boiling water with the frozen strawberries.
Let stand until jelly-like. Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Store in the fridge until ready to use.

title: lemon butter trout
directions: Combine butter, lemon juice, parsley, dill and black pepper. On a 12 x 12-inch square aluminum foil, shape butter mixture into 1-inch log.
Wrap tightly in foil and freeze for 1 hour.
Broil trout, meat side up, for about 5 minutes.
Serve topped with 2 slices herb butter.
Serves 6.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with apple wedges.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix well.
Top with mixture of topping ingredients.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sour cream.
Mix next 4 ingredients together; add to Cool Whip mixture.
Fold in fruit and freeze. Take out of freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: "aunt diane's terrific tuna noodle casserole"
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water.
Drain.
Combine macaroni, tuna, mayo, veggies and salt.
Blend soup and milk; heat through. Add to macaroni mixture.
Add cheese and sprinkle some on top. Turn into casserole dish.
Bake at 425°, uncovered, about 20 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix well and place dough in a large greased bowl.
Cover with a towel.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, punch down and divide into 3 loaves.
Knead each loaf 12 times.
Put into greased loaf pans.
Let rise 4 to 6 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Brush with melted butter while hot, if desired.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix sour cream and soup mix together and chill for about 1 hour.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream margarine and peanut butter with mixer.
Add 1 cup of the flour.
Add sugars, eggs, baking powder, and soda.
Add vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly combines.
Beat in remaining flour.
If necessary, cover and chill dough until easy to handle. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in additional sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 7 to 9 minutes.
Immediately press 1 Kiss into each cookie.
Cool on wire racks. Makes 5 dozen.

title: swiss enchiladas
directions: Saute onion until soft in oil.
Add garlic clove, tomato puree, green chilies and chopped chicken.
Season with salt and simmer 10 minutes.
Fry tortillas fresh in about 1-inch of hot oil. Do not let them crisp, as they are to be rolled.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in three cups of hot cream.
Dip each tortilla in this.
Cover generously with chicken filling and roll up.
Arrange rolls in baking dish and pour remaining cream mixture over them. Top with Jack or Swiss cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
If you wish, garnish with avocado slices or hard-cooked eggs, radishes and ripe green olives.
Serves 6.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: corn tamale pie
directions: Break tamales in pieces.
Mix with corn and beaten eggs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole; sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until center is firm.
Garnish with ripe olives, if desired.

title: fried pie pastry
directions: Mix all ingredients and divide into 10 balls.
Roll out and use 2 teaspoons of fruit filling for each pie.
Fry in deep fat or oil.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat egg yellows and add to milk.
Mix sugar and flour together and gradually add to milk.
Cook in a double boiler 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Will thicken.
Add vanilla flavoring to taste and yellow food coloring as desired.
Pour through strainer and refrigerate.

title: tagliatelle with jumbo prawns
directions: 1. Cook pasta according to package directions.
2. In skillet saute the shallot with olive oil & butter as
soon as it browns. Add the shrimp and cook for four
minutes.
3. Gently stir in the cream then turn off the heat. Add
salt and pepper as desired.
4. Dress the pasta with the prepared sauce and serve.

title: hash brown au gratin
directions: Thaw potatoes.
In large mixing bowl, combine potatoes, salt, pepper, onion and cheese.
In medium mixing bowl, combine 1/2 cup melted butter, sour cream and soup.
Pour over potato mixture and mix gently.
Pour into 3 quart buttered casserole.

title: peach praline muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Generously butter a muffin tin. Combine yogurt, eggs, and the large quick bread mix packet and 1/3 cup of the swirl packet (small packet). Beat until well mixed. Spoon into muffin cups, filling about 2/3 full.
Sprinkle remaining swirl mixture over top of each muffin.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into center of muffin comes out clean.
Remove from pan immediately.
Serve warm with butter.

title: baked consomme rice
directions: Place all ingredients in a buttered casserole with cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Take out 1 cup of this mixture and stir in beaten egg yolks.
Pour back into saucepan.
Cook at gentle boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.

title: angel hash
directions: Drain fruit and reserve juice.
In large saucepan, mix cornstarch and water.
Add egg and juice; blend well.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool thoroughly. Stir in Cool Whip, nuts, coconut, marshmallows and drained fruit and pineapple.
Place in serving bowl; cover and chill overnight.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix above ingredients; drop by spoonfuls into hot grease until brown.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan, bake 375° for 75 minutes until brown and crispy.

title: butter cookies
directions: Gradually add powdered sugar to butter.
Cream well. Add 1 unbeaten egg, vanilla and sifted flour.
Stir in pecans and candied cherries.
Chill 1 hour.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Shape in rolls and roll in wax paper.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Slice for cookies and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 13 or 15 minutes until edges begin to show a little brown.
Will keep in freezer for future use.

title: grandma's refrigerator rolls
directions: Place water in large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast, stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, salt, butter, eggs, whole wheat flour and enough all-purpose white flour to make stiff dough.
Grease bowl and top.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 hours or up to 3 days.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Line muffin tins with liners.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until blended.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour over wafers filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes. Remove from pan when cool.
Top with fruit, nuts or preserves.
Be creative.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix all together and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
"Nuts or raisins may be added if desired."

title: potatoes and onions
directions: Wash and slice potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Do onions same way.
Place a potato slice then onion slice until all is placed in dish.
Pour melted butter over potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, then paprika over ingredients.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: quick brown bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, sugar, salt and soda together. Add buttermilk. Pour batter into greased and floured 8-ounce coffee cans. Fill half full. Bake 45 to 60 minutes. Remove from can and cool. Use coffee cans or loaf pans; loaf pans will be longer to bake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: If zucchini is large and old, peel before using.
Blend eggs, oil,
sugar,
zucchini and vanilla.
Fold in nuts.	Sift dry ingredients
and
fold
lightly
into batter. Bake in loaf pans for about 1 hour in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: quick and easy spanish rice and beef
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet. Add tomatoes, water, corn and seasonings. Bring to a boil and boil about 2 minutes.
Stir in rice. Cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
While biscuits are baking, mix margarine and garlic powder; remove biscuits from oven and brush tops with margarine immediately (before removing from the cookie sheet).
Serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.
These resemble the biscuits served at the Red Lobster.

title: noodle casserole
directions: In pan put a small amount of Pam or cooking oil.
Put cut up onion and ground meat in pan.
Brown; then add tomatoes and tomato soup.
Cook macaroni in boiling water until done.
Mix all in a large bowl.
Put in a 2 1/2-quart casserole and reheat in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Can be heated in microwave.

title: cool carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water with salt until tender.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients together in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Pour mixture over carrots.
Let stand 45 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
Lasts "indefinitely."

title: shrimp and noodle bake
directions: Saute garlic in small amount olive oil.
Add shrimp for a few minutes.
Add tomatoes and rotini.
Put on serving dish and sprinkle with Feta cheese. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: chocolate truffle and caramel pie
directions: Combine crumbs, pecans and melted butter.
Press into bottom and up sides of 10-inch pie plate.
Cook in microwave on High for 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.

title: broiler icing
directions: Mix all together; spread on any 13 x 9-inch cake.
Put under broiler until brown.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pack vegetables and salt in sterilized jars.
Cover with vinegar solution.
Place in water bath for 10 minutes.

title: frosty cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, pineapple, sugar and marshmallows.
Let chill overnight.

title: big boy strawberry pie
directions: Wash and stem the berries; set aside.
Combine the sugar and 1 cup water.
Stir in the paste made with the cornstarch and 1/2 cup water.
Boil gently until thick and clear, about 5 minutes.
Stir in jello.
Cool a little.
Fold in the berries and pour into the baked pie shell.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Rinse chicken pieces and pat dry.
Season with salt and paprika.
Place sliced vegetables and bay leaf in crock-pot. Place chicken pieces on top of vegetables.
Pour in chicken broth. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce; let simmer. Boil macaroni.
Cut Cheddar cheese into small pieces.
Drain macaroni.
Place in baking dish; mix ground beef and Cheddar cheese with noodles.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and a few pats of butter.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with warm biscuits.

title: mexican dip
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients. If too thick, add a little water.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot rolls
directions: Scald milk with sugar and shortening.
When lukewarm, add yeast and let stand about 5 minutes.
Stir in 4 cups flour (or enough to make stiff batter), egg and salt. Sprinkle board with small amount of flour and work dough into ball.
Let rise.
Make out into rolls and let rise.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken and broccoli au gratin
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onions until transparent. Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, curry powder and pepper. Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add water to make 1/2 cup liquid.

title: sesame broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling, salted water until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain.
In saucepan, combine oil, vinegar, soy sauce, sugar and sesame seed.
Heat to boiling; pour over broccoli.
Turn spears to coat.
Serves 5, 74 calories per serving.

title: un-fried catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray the vegetable oil over the baking sheet 3 times to coat.
Put the cornmeal, thyme and basil on a large plate and mix well.
Sprinkle 1/8 tsp. of the garlic powder, 1/8 tsp. of the lemon pepper and 1 tsp. of the blackening seasoning on each catfish filet.
Coat the filets thoroughly with the cornmeal mixture and transfer them to the prepared baking sheet. Dust each filet with 1/8 tsp. of paprika.
Coat the catfish lightly with the cooking spray.
Place the baking sheet on the bottom shelf of oven.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for about 5 minutes more, until the crust is golden and the fish flakes easily.

title: creamy spinach bake
directions: In a bowl, beat the cream cheese until smooth. Add the soup mix; mix well. Stir in spinach and onions. Transfer to a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine cracker crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over spinach mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce and water.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, Ricotta cheese, spinach and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, stirring well. Set aside.
Spread 1 cup tomato mixture in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer half each of uncooked lasagna noodles, spinach mixture, Mozzarella cheese and tomato mixture; repeat layers.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover dish securely with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let lasagna stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: apple raisin slaw
directions: Mix apples with lemon juice in a large bowl.
Add rest of ingredients and mix lightly.

title: onion casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Butter casserole dish and line with crushed crackers.
Add onions and soup in layers.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle crackers and cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: gourmet goulash
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add meat; brown well.
Add onion.
Combine other ingredients (except sour cream).
Add to meat and onion; cook, covered, until meat is tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
If desired, add sour cream.
Serve with parsley buttered noodles.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: *Can substitute with tuna.

title: low-fat oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together the first 5 ingredients. In another bowl, with electric mixer, cream margarine, brown sugar and Sweet One.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients, then raisins. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto baking sheets sprayed with Pam.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.
Calories: 55 per cookie.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Dissolve Junkets in 2 teaspoons water; set aside.
Mash bananas in a bowl and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Add bananas, then the Junket mixture.
Pour into freezing container of home ice cream maker.
Follow freezing directions recommended by the manufacturer of the ice cream maker.

title: holiday wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes 5 1/2 quarts.

title: bananas foster
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar in a skillet over medium heat and caramelize.
Add orange juice and creme de banana.
Add walnuts, bananas and rum; flame (optional) agitating pan slightly. Put ice cream into individual bowls and spoon mixture over ice cream.
Serve warm.
(Serves 6.)

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill and churn.
Freeze.

title: cheeseburger and fries casserole
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch pan, layer as follows:
hamburger, soup, French fries, cheese, hamburger, soup and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: okra salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Fry okra.
Chop onion, tomatoes and pepper. Toss together and serve.
No dressing.
Tomatoes serve as dressing.
Serve hot or cold (I like it better hot).

title: fruit shake
directions: Pre-chill all fruits.
Put all ingredients in blender; blend on medium speed for 30 seconds, then whip at high speed for 10 seconds.
Makes 3 servings.

title: chocolate fudge candy
directions: Mix first 4 items. Bring to a boil, then lower heat to medium. Let cook until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cool water. (Stir frequently.) Pour into buttered dish and let cool. Cut into squares.

title: garden slaw
directions: To make the dressing, soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Mix sugar, vinegar and spices in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in softened gelatin.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Beat well.
Gradually beat in oil.

title: barbecue deer
directions: Place meat in casserole dish. Cover with water.
Add vinegar, pepper, salt and lemon pepper. Cook 4 hours at 350°.
Make sure meat is very tender.
Drain. Add barbecue sauce.
Good over rice or as a sandwich.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs & sugar until creamy.
Combine flour, baking soda and cocoa, add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: north dakota sunflower pie
directions: Beat together eggs, brown sugar, corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Spread sunflower kernels evenly in the bottom of the unbaked pie shell.
Pour in the sugar mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until center is almost set (it will jiggle slightly).

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice and salt.
Chill.
When slightly thickened, add pineapple and carrots. Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Cut into individual servings and place on lettuce.
May be served with a teaspoon of salad dressing on the side.

title: chess pie or tarts
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add cornmeal, vinegar and vanilla. Add the eggs, one at a time.
Pour into 16 frozen tart shells. Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: papa's oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan. Add drained oysters and heat until edges curl. Add milk, salt and pepper.
Heat but do not boil. Sprinkle each serving with paprika.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown the roast and put into a large cooking pot with lid. Add nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves, onion, wine and bouillon.
Cook 1 hour at 350°, then add carrots and potatoes.
Cook 5 hours at 250°.

title: after school snack
directions: Spread peanut butter over crackers, then put marshmallows on them and microwave until marshmallows are melted.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Add rest of ingredients (except nuts).
Mix well; stir in nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and chunk sweet potatoes. Cook until tender (add salt to water when cooking). While potatoes are cooking mix together corn flakes, raisins, nuts, brown sugar and butter. Set aside. Mash the potatoes; add sugar, milk, eggs cinnamon, nutmeg and beat well. Spoon into a greased casserole dish. Top with corn flake mixture. Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: loose meat sandwich
directions: Brown hamburg (loose).
Add onion soup mix and chicken gumbo soup.
Allow to cool down.
Thicken, if desired, with cornstarch. Place mixture in hot dog buns and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together well shortening, eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and sour milk, mashed bananas and nuts.
Mix well. Grease loaf pan and coat with flour.
Put batter in pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Let cool and remove from pan.

title: fluffy white icing(frosting for  chocolate nugget cake)
directions: Boil slowly sugar, water & cream of tartar, without stirring until syrup spins to 8 inch threads.
Keep saucepan covered first 3 minutes to prevent crystals from forming on sides of pan.
Remove from heat.

title: white icing
directions: Beat butter and Crisco; add sugar a little at a time.
Add warm milk, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add vanilla.
Beat almost 10 minutes.

title: microwave fish fillets
directions: You will need Saran Wrap.

title: polish kolaches
directions: Blend yeast and sugar in a large bowl.
Add melted shortening, beaten egg yolks, lukewarm milk, mashed potatoes and water (from boiled potatoes).
Blend.
Add 3 cups flour, salt, baking powder and stir.
Add remainder of flour and knead into a big ball. Place in a greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled in size; place on floured board.
Cut into buns the size of tennis balls and place on greased pan.
Grease buns and let rise double in size.
Make depressions on top of buns with fingers for filling; put in any fruit filling.
Cherry pie filling with a powdered sugar glaze is a favorite.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients well, adding enough sweet milk to make soft, but not running.
Drop small amounts from the end of a teaspoon into very hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: joan's lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain excess grease.
Add spaghetti sauce and let simmer.
Cook noodles according to directions on package. Cool slightly in cold water in order to be able to handle.
Place a small amount of the sauce in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Then layer, in the following order:
noodles, sauce, Cheddar cheese, noodles, sauce, Mozzarella, noodles, sauce, Parmesan and remaining Cheddar and Mozzarella.
Bake about 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot.

title: biscuits
directions: Knead 10 times and bake for 15 minutes at 425°.

title: lemon bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 4 minutes. Bake in well-greased Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes or so. Let cool in pan 5 to 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix
margarine,
oatmeal and boiling water together and let stand 20 minutes, then add eggs, white sugar, brown sugar, flour, salt,
soda,
cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Beat well. Grease pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in long pan.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Combine pecan halves, candied cherries, seedless raisins and 1/2 cup flour.
Let stand.
Measure and sift together ground cloves, nutmeg, 3 1/2 cups flour, allspice, soda and cinnamon. Work until smooth.
Beat together until light and fluffy, butter and brown sugar.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with whiskey.
Blend in fruit.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Store in layers separated by wax paper.

title: muffin scalloped corn
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: anzac biscuits
directions: Melt butter and syrup in a large saucepan.
Mix bicarbonate of soda with boiling water and add to melted butter. This will froth up, so make sure saucepan is large enough.
Mix dry ingredients and add to saucepan.
Mix well to make a firm consistency. Drop teaspoonfuls onto well-greased baking trays, leaving space to spread.
Bake in a moderate oven for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Loosen on trays while still hot and allow to cool on trays, then transfer to wire racks and allow to cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake and cool pie shell.
Crush enough berries; add sugar and water and bring to boil.
Thicken with cornstarch dissolved in water.
Boil until clear.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Place remaining berries in pie shell.
When mixture cools, pour over berries.
Do not put hot mixture over berries; it cooks them.
Cool pie and top with whipped cream.

title: boze milosti(divine love krispies)
directions: Mix eggs with cream and water.
Add to flour and salt.
Stir and knead on floured board until smooth.
Roll out very thin.
Cut in diamond shapes (3 x 3-inch).
Make a 2-inch slit in center of each piece.
Fry in hot oil, stretching dough still thinner as you drop into oil.
Fry until golden.
Dry on paper towels.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar or drizzle with thin powdered sugar icing.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine salmon, cheese, salt, horseradish, grated onion, lemon juice and Ranch dressing.
Let chill.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts and parsley flakes.

title: easy tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour, then drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breasts with all ingredients for 6 hours. Better results are obtained if every chicken breast is cut in two halves and pounded, to thin the breast to no more than 1 centimeter thickness.

title: healthy chili
directions: Brown meat.
Pour off any fat and saute onion and garlic with the meat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1
hour.

title: stuffed rolls
directions: Mix ingredients with mayonnaise to spread.
Stuff buttered rolls.
Wrap filled rolls in wax paper.
Heat for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water to boil.
Mix other ingredients together.
Add raisins and water; mix in flour.
Drop onto cookie sheet (greased cookie sheets).
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: scallops de jonghe
directions: Combine crumbs, onions, parsley and seasonings.
Add butter and sherry; mix thoroughly.
Combine crumb mixture and scallops; toss lightly.
Place in well-greased, shallow, 1-quart casserole. Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly browned. Makes 6 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Using a 3-quart pot, boil rice, cinnamon stick and the lemon peel in cold water on medium-high heat.
Continue to cook until rice is soft and most of the water has evaporated.
Remove cinnamon stick.
Add milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Continue cooking at medium-low heat, stirring often until thick.
Remove the lemon peel.
Serve in 8 dessert dishes and sprinkle with the powdered cinnamon when serving.

title: peach muffins
directions: Chop peaches; drain and set aside.
Combine flour, salt, soda and sugar in mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil; stir until dry ingredients are well moistened.
Add peaches and remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Spoon batter evenly into greased or paper lined muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes one dozen.

title: creamy cheesy potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes, celery and onion with water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook on medium-high heat until potatoes are tender.
Reduce heat to low and add soup, cheese, milk and margarine.
Simmer until cheese has melted, stirring occasionally.

title: black bottom cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan or place papers in cupcake pans.
Beat together cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt until fluffy.
Stir in chocolate chips.
In another bowl, beat the remaining ingredients except the flour.
Beat flour in last.
If making in 13 x 9-inch pan, pour batter into baking dish.
Drop cream cheese mixture by spoonfuls into the batter.
Bake approximately 45 minutes.
If making mini cupcakes or regular-size cupcakes, pour chocolate batter in until half full.
Drop a small amount of cream cheese batter in center.
For mini cupcakes, bake 15 minutes.
For regular-size, bake 25 to 30 minutes.
(Makes 24 cakes.)

title: old-fashion caramel pie
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, salt and flour well.
Add milk.
Mix and set aside.
Melt 3/4 cup sugar in a heavy skillet
over medium heat until
melted and brown.
Stir constantly. When sugar is melted, add the milk mixture (sugar will crystallize).
Stir until dissolved and of correct texture.
Remove from heat.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and butter.
Mix well and pour into baked pie shells.
Add meringue and brown top.
Makes 2 pies!

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Separate the fiber from unwashed pumpkin seeds. Add to 2 cups pumpkin seeds the butter and salt. Spread in a shallow pan. Bake in very slow oven at 250°
until crisp and brown.
Stir often.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
May be topped with cheese of any kind and sliced tomatoes for decoration.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat the first 10 ingredients for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Batter will be thick.
With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove cool cakes, fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: bad bob's hot wing sauce
directions: Mix together. Put over cooked wings.

title: coffee cake
directions: Thoroughly grease angel food pan.
Arrange frozen yeast rolls in bottom.
Sprinkle over the rolls
sugar, mixed with cinnamon. Then sprinkle over it the pudding.
Add nuts.
Dot with butter or margarine, cut into pieces.
Place pan in cold oven overnight.
In morning, bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn out onto platter and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce to 350° for additional 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: egg noodle-broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion and saute over medium heat for 3 minutes. Add water and bouillon.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally until bouillon is dissolved.
Gradually add noodles and salt so that bouillon continues to boil.
Cook uncovered for 3 minutes stirring occasionally.
Stir in broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook 4 more minutes.
Add milk, cheese and pepper and cook until cheese melts.

title: pot pie dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder well and work in shortening. Add egg and water to make a stiff dough.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick; cut in 2-inch squares and drop in boiling broth carefully so they don't stick.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage with sawmill gravy
directions: Brown and drain sausage, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings in the pan.
Blend in flour to make a roux.
Add milk and blend until smooth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer for 2 minutes.
Serve over hot, open-faced biscuits.

title: jerry glenn's favorite baked beans and sausage
directions: Parboil sausage to eliminate some excess fats.
Cut into 1-inch chunks.
Mix all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and thinly slice.
Add water, vinegar and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add salt, pepper and onion powder to taste.
Chill 3 hours to allow flavors to mix.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a blender or food processor, blend the cookies until they are finely crushed.
Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.

title: apple rolls
directions: Melt butter in a bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk, melted butter, 6 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 egg and whole wheat flour.
Stir to blend.
Add the all-purpose flour.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Let rise in a warm place for about 40 minutes.
Punch down.

title: squash souffle
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine squash, butter, brown sugar, salt, pepper and orange peel.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Carefully fold into squash mixture.
Bake souffle in 350° oven for 30 minutes to 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: quick and easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream and mix.
Layer vanilla wafers, thin slices of bananas and pudding mix in 8 x 12-inch dish.
Repeat with another layer.
Let set overnight.

title: weight watchers crab crostini
directions: Preheat the broiler.
Line a broiler pan with foil.
Pick over the crabmeat to remove any cartilage.
In a medium bowl, combine the crabmeat, bell pepper, mayonnaise, parsley, chives, lime juice, mustard, Parmesan cheese and hot pepper sauce and blend well.

title: date cake
directions: Mix walnuts, dates and soda in boiling water.
Add to mayonnaise, sugar, flour, cinnamon and chocolate.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and microwave for 9 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave 3 more minutes.
Quickly stir in baking soda until becomes foamy.
Spread on greased cookie sheet. Let cool.

title: deviled ham twists
directions: Slice a zucchini longways.
Prepare an egg wash:
egg, 1 tablespoon flour, salt and pepper.
Dip zucchini in egg wash and fry both sides in a pan of oil.
Roll up like a jelly roll and put toothpick in.
Make a marinade of lemon juice and oil. Drizzle this marinade over the roll-ups.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, sift together the flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg; mix well. Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remaining mixture on bottom of prepared pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage and ground beef.
Drain. Melt cheese, stir in taco sauce and soup.
Add meat and heat until warmed through.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all but chips and cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chips and cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Serve with salad and rolls.

title: mexican baked potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Add margarine.
Place over medium-high heat until melted.
Add red pepper and green onions; saute until tender.
Stir in corn, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Saute until tender.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Stir in sour cream and cilantro; set aside.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread according to directions.
Let cool.
Chop vegetables.
Mix all together.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir in margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form into a crust on sides and bottom of a 10-inch pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper until tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt. Heat through.
Pour over cottage cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Blend first 2 ingredients.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into 2 loaf pans or 3 (1 pound) coffee cans which have been well-greased. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Slide bread out of pans or cans and cool.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and green pepper; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, catsup and pepper; heat.
Alternate meat mixture and cheese slices in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange biscuits around edge of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: s-o-o-o-o  easy chocolate chip cookies!!!
directions: Mix all ingredients until moistened.
Drop by teaspoonfuls (soup spoon) onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients (flour, salt and soda).
Set aside.
Cream well shortening and oleo.
Add and cream until fluffy the sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add the flour mixture with 2 teaspoons milk. Mix very well. Drop walnut size balls of dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes; do not overbake.

title: eggs portugal
directions: Whip milk, eggs and dry mustard together.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bread cubes; layer cheese on top, then layer sausage over cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, mix soup and broth together and pour over all.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: smoked beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan 9 x 9 x 2-inches. Mix 2 cups
bisquick,
sour
cream
and water until soft dough forms. Beat
strokes.
Spread
in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about
25 minutes.
Heat margarine in pan until melted. Stir in 1/4
cup
Bisquick,
the onion and seasoning.
Heat to boiling, stirring
constantly;
remove
from heat.
Gradually stir in milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in 1 cup of cheese until melted.
Stir in beef,
peas and corn;
heat through.
Spread over baked layer; sprinkle
with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted, 3 to 5 minutes. Serve immediately.
Yields 9 servings.

title: strawberry banana bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Set aside.
Combine soda, milk, bananas and dry jello.
Add this mixture to creamed mixture.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to banana mixture.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all this together and roll into long roll, then roll in chili powder.

title: chicken delight
directions: Boil chicken with salt and pepper.
Remove bones and skin and dice.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly; salt and pepper to taste. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: chocolate swirl cheese pie
directions: Add sugar to cheese
in
bowl, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla. Measure 2 cups of
cheese
mixture;
fold
in chocolate.
Pour remaining cheese mixture into well-buttered 10-inch pie pan or 9-inch square pan.
Add
spoonfuls
of
the
chocolate-cheese mixture and zigzag a
spatula
through
batter
to
marble it. Bake at 350° for 40
to
45 minutes; cool, then chill.
Cut in wedges.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion, green pepper and carrots.
Mix other ingredients and toss with vegetables; chill.

title: fabulous fudge(microwave)
directions: In microwave bowl, combine chocolate chips with condensed milk and salt.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes; stir thoroughly. Microwave for another 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Line an 8 or 9-inch pan with aluminum foil and put contents into pan.
Cool to room temperature.
Remove foil and cut into squares. Makes about 2 pounds.
I do not refrigerate the fudge to cool it. It stays creamy if not refrigerated.

title: peppered rib-eye steaks
directions: Brush steaks lightly with oil.
Combine garlic powder, paprika, thyme, oregano, salt, black, lemon and red pepper; sprinkle over and press into both sides of steaks.
Place in glass baking dish; cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Place steaks on grill over medium-low coals.
Cover.
Grill 16 to 20 minutes for rare to medium rare, turning halfway through cooking time.
Transfer steaks to warm serving platter and garnish with orange slices and parsley sprigs.
Serve with spinach salad and Italian bread.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour over chicken wings in baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Recipe is for 3 pounds of chicken wings.)

title: prune cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and line with wax paper.
Beat shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs and mix again.
Sift dry ingredients and alternate flour and milk.
Stir in prunes.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: caldo gallego soup
directions: Place ham, chorizos and salt pork in water.
Cook 30 minutes. Add greens and beans.
Saute onion and pepper until transparent in olive oil.
Add to greens.
Peel and cut potatoes in small cubes. Add to soup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: sugar-free rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Stir occasionally the first hour.
Or, microwave on Low for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Turn dish a quarter turn every 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally the first 15 minutes.
Serves 9.
Diabetic exchange: 1 milk and 1/2 fruit.
Calories per serving: 111.

title: surprise beets
directions: Combine cornstarch and pineapple juice; add 3/4 cup beet juice.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut chess bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Pour the remainder of ingredients on first mixture after mixing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar together.
Beat Crisco until creamy, then add sugar gradually.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with crushed bananas.
When well blended, pour batter into greased loaf pan, 8 x 4 x 3-inch. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Put flour on vegetables.
Saute vegetables in butter and cook until tender.
Add shrimp; cook until done.
Add stewed tomatoes and season to taste.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve on rice.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix together pretzels, sugar and melted butter.
Press in 9
x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Beat together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour over cooled pretzel mixture.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Pour over mixture.

title: hidden valley party mix
directions: Combine mix and oil, then add dill weed, garlic powder and lemon pepper.
Pour over crackers and stir.
Put in warm oven and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Use your imagination.
Use other kinds of small crackers, your favorites.

title: strawberry shortcakes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix Bisquick, sugar, margarine and milk until soft dough forms.
Gently smooth dough into ball on cloth covered board, dusted with Bisquick.
Knead.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick, cut with 3-inch cutter dipped in Bisquick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Split shortcakes. Spoon strawberries between halves and on tops.
Top with cream.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Roll into balls and brown in oil; pour tomato sauce over balls and add 1 can water.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together flour, salt and sugar.
Add eggs, cocktail and juice and vanilla.
Pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix 3 tablespoons of butter with granulated sugar. Mix flour, baking powder and salt thoroughly.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Spread batter evenly in a greased 8-inch square greased pan.

title: beans 'n turkey
directions: Cook beans until done.
Brown ground turkey.
Add tomatoes, bouillon, onion, garlic, cumin and chili powder.
Mix all together, heat through and enjoy.

title: year round cabbage slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, onion, pepper and pimento.
Set aside. In pan mix honey, oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Boil hard 1 minute.
Pour over slaw.
Mix well.
Seal in refrigerator for 3 days.
Good until it is used up.

title: pickled beets
directions: Add water to beet liquid to make 2 cups or to cover beets. Heat liquid.
Add sugar, vinegar and cinnamon.
Heat to boiling and pour over beets.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 12 hours. Optional - add hard boiled eggs or slices of onion.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Add Jell-O and cool.
Pour over fresh strawberries in prepared pie shell (about 2 cups of halved strawberries).

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain both cans of fruit and pineapple; put in bowl.
Save 1 cup of juice from pineapple.
Cook 1 small box vanilla with 1 cup pineapple juice until it's clear.
Pour over fruit.

title: the best dinner rolls
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add yeast (dissolved in water).
Stir in flour.
Cover and let set overnight.
Divide dough into six balls; roll out and cut into pie wedges.
Roll wedges to center.
Let these stand until they double in size (2 to 4 hours).
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 425°.

title: make ahead crab casserole
directions: Combine crab with cooked noodles, olives, almonds, chopped eggs and sherry.
Fold in white sauce and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Turn into buttered casserole and sprinkle mixture with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Arrange layers of potatoes, onions and soup mixture.
Add salt, pepper and paprika as desired. Dot with butter.
Cover, bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix 1/2 cup flour with fruit.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and fruit.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: christmas pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Add dry mixture, then add cherries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: special baked beans
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bake until bubbly at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Top with Doritos.
