Make sure ground beef is cool before adding other ingredients.

title: ice cream tortoni
directions: Mix together almonds, butter, crushed vanilla wafers and extract.
Reserve 1/4 cup mixture for topping.
Sprinkle 1/2 of remaining mixture over bottom of a foil-lined 8 x 8-inch pan. Spoon 1/2 of the ice cream over crumbs.
Drizzle with 1/2 of the preserves.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Repeat ice cream and preserves layers.
Sprinkle with reserved 1/4 cup crumbs.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 9 squares.

title: brussels sprouts with almonds
directions: Bring 1-inch water to boil in large, deep skillet.
Add sprouts, cover and cook over medium-high heat for 8 to 10 minutes. Drain.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add lemon juice, salt, almonds and sprouts.
Stir over medium-high heat for 2 to 3 minutes until sprouts are hot.

title: bourbon pecan pie
directions: Toss pecans and bourbon until coated; let stand 1 hour, until most of the bourbon is absorbed.
Heat oven to 325°.
Mix brown sugar and flour; beat in margarine until creamy.
Beat in corn syrup, eggs and salt; stir in pecan mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Cover edge with 1/2-inch aluminum foil strip to prevent excessive browning.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Remove foil last 15 minutes.

title: pork chops cacciatore
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops.
Slice pepper and add chopped onion, drained mushrooms, sauce and spices.
Stir and cover. Simmer until pork chops are tender.
Serve over wide noodles.

title: my mother's old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Cream together sugar, molasses and margarine.
Sift the dry ingredients.
Start adding dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Add along the hot water and soda.
When all is mixed well, have eggs beaten and add at the last.
Stir in good.

title: butter cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar; add unbeaten egg.
Beat well and add sifted ingredients slowly.
Blend well and add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes (watch closely, they burn easily) or until lightly browned.
Let cookies sit for a few minutes before removing to rack.

title: granola cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, honey, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in rolled oats, coconut, raisins, wheat germ and nuts.

title: dog food casserole
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Spread meat in 9 x 13-inch pan; next, spread corn.
Pour soup (undiluted) over meat and corn. Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ravioli
directions: Cook meat, onions and peppers.
Boil macaroni and drain.
Salt and pepper meat.
Mix altogether and put in casserole.

title: cherry delight
directions: Prepare instant pudding according to directions on box and add the sour cream.
Break angel food cake in pieces and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with pudding and sour cream mix, Cool Whip and top with cherry pie filling.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Do not overbeat.
Drop into hot 350° oil and fry until hush puppies float to the top.
You may need to turn over several times.
Drain and serve hot.

title: sweet and sour wings
directions: Cut tips and sever wings to joint, making two mini drumsticks. Dip wings in egg and then cornstarch to which garlic salt has been added.
Brown wings and place in a 10 x 10-inch pan.
Cover with sauce made of next 6 ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter. Mix sugar and eggs together; add melted butter. Sift together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. Beat. Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: polish stuffed cabbage
directions: Saute onions in oleo, then add to meat, rice, salt and pepper. Mix well. Core cabbage, then boil head in water for 10 minutes. Drain and separate leaves. Place a large tablespoon of meat mixture in each leaf and roll up, tucking in ends. Place rolls and bay leaf in baking dish. Mix soup with 1/2 can of water and 1 teaspoon sugar, then pour over rolls. Cover and bake at 350° for about 90 minutes. Check periodically and add more water if needed.

title: skillet chicken salad
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter until sizzling. Stir in chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and fork-tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients except lettuce leaves and cherry tomatoes.
On platter or individual salad plates, place lettuce leaves.
Place chicken salad on lettuce. Arrange cherry tomatoes around salad.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix
butter, brown sugar and flour to make
the
crumbs for the topping.
Mix table syrup, egg, baking soda in boiling water. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle crumbs
on top. Start baking at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat
to 300° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into large chunks.
Place in a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Pour butter over and toss until well coated. Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: german potato dumplings
directions: Boil potatoes until soft enough to mash.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Shape into balls.
Roll lightly into flour and cook in rapidly boiling water for 15 minutes.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Stir in eggs, milk, bread pieces, salt, mustard and cheese.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Must be mixed the night before and refrigerated.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Spread the fruit pie filling evenly in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Spread the dry cake mix evenly over the pie filling.
Pour the melted margarine over the dry cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 20 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Enjoy!

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up and steam cabbage in salt water until crisp; drain. Butter a casserole bottom and layer with cabbage.
Nest cover cabbage with sour cream, then a layer of shredded cheese, then soda crackers.
Continue to layer in this order until soda crackers are on top layer.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: mocha sauce
directions: In small saucepan, over low heat, melt butter. Stir in sugar, whipping cream and cocoa.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in instant coffee and vanilla.
Serve warm or cool. Cover.
Refrigerate leftover sauce.
Yields 2 cups sauce.

title: chocolate raspberry brownies
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Melt butter and chocolate in a heavy, large saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Whisk in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in small bowl; add to chocolate mixture and whisk to blend.
Stir in nuts.
Pour 2 cups batter into pan.
Freeze until firm, about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt at high speed of mixer until soft peaks form. Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form. Sift cocoa over egg white mixture; fold in. Fold in mini-chips. Cover a baking sheet with parchment paper. Drop batter by level tablespoonfuls onto prepared baking sheet. Bake for 40 minutes. Cool on wire rack. Store in an airtight container.

title: bread i
directions: Make as any
other
bread.
(Let
rise, work down, etc.) Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tarragon potatoes
directions: Using a vegetable peeler, peel away just enough skin from the circumference of each potato to form a stripe.
Place potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with cold water.
Over high heat, bring potatoes to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat to medium; partially cover and cook potatoes 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine butter, minced shallots, minced fresh tarragon, salt and ground black pepper to make a paste.
Add warm potatoes to bowl.
Toss ingredients gently until seasonings are evenly distributed.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill in ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add pineapple and blueberries; congeal.

title: old-fashion tea cakes
directions: Sift flour.
Add sugar, eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Work up like biscuit dough using milk as needed.
Roll out and cut with shaped cutters.
You can add nuts, coconut or candied fruit, if desired.
Bake slowly at 350°.
The thinner you flatten, the crispier they are.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Melt butter; beat eggs. Add flour mixture to eggs and butter.
Add milk and vanilla; beat good.
Add coconut and pecans; stir well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: laura's homemade chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Stir flour with baking soda and salt, set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter with sugar and brown sugar at medium speed until creamy and lightened in color.
About 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, mix on low speed until incorporated.
Gradually blend dry mixture into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry pudding mix.
Stir well.
Add undrained pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a serving dish and place in refrigerator for two hours.

title: fruit pie
directions: Combine eggs, butter, raisins, nuts, coconut, sugar and vinegar in a mixing bowl.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix together chocolate chips and butterscotch chips and melt. Pour melted chips over chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Quickly form mound with fingers.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown chops and place in baking dish.
Top with chop with a slice of tomato and ring of bell pepper.
Fill pepper ring with rice.
Mix mushroom soup with 2 to 2 1/2 cans of water; pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wholesome banana bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil in a medium bowl.
Beat with mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add egg and beat until light and lemon colored.
With mixer running at low speed, add flour mixture alternately with bananas, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Blend well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with wheat germ on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until cake tester is clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; let cool completely before slicing.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add margarine or butter to boiling water
and stir over medium heat until margarine melts and water comes
to a second boil. Combine flour and salt;
add to water-margarine mixture all
at once. Stir vigorously until mixture
leaves
sides
of pan. Remove from heat and add eggs, one at
a
time,
beating thoroughly
after each addition.
Drop
mixture
by
teaspoons onto
cookie
sheet.
Bake in 350° oven
until
light
brown. Remove from cookie sheet and stuff with whipped cream, pudding or custard.

title: holiday stuffed turkey
directions: To prepare stuffing:
In one quart saucepan, over medium heat, cook mushrooms and onion with savory and nutmeg in hot butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add broccoli, stuffing, rice and broth. Toss to mix well.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and place in greased baking dish. Brown meat and onion. Stir in rice. Pour on top of cabbage. Mix soup and water and pour over other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add more water if casserole is too dry.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken fettucini
directions: Cook noodles until almost done; cut chicken into 1-inch cubes and saute in 1/8 cup oil with garlic, mushrooms, onions and salt and pepper to taste.
When onions are tender and chicken has no pink, add a jar of sauce and noodles.
Stir until thoroughly mixed. Place in a Dutch oven (ovenproof) or very large covered ovenproof dish.
Cover with slices of cheese until top is completely covered. Bake for 30 minutes covered and 30 minutes uncovered at 375°. Serves 12.

title: jiffy brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and pour into greased and lightly floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut while still hot.

title: angel punch
directions: Blend strawberries, lemonade and ice cream in blender.
Place in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over blended ingredients and mix. Makes 25 small cups.

title: marie's russian dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Store in airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: pizza dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast over "very warm" water.
Stir to dissolve yeast.
Stir flour and salt together.
Add yeast mixture and oil. Stir until rough dough forms.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 to 7 minutes). Shape into ball and place in greased bowl; turn to coat.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes. Spread in 16-inch pan.
Add toppings.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tomato and green pepper salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass or plastic bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Melt butter; saute onion until clear.
Add soup, mushrooms with liquid and cheese (cut into chunks).
Cook over low heat until cheese melts and all is heated.
Add well drained, cooked broccoli.
Serve hot in chafing dish with Fritos and Wheat Thins.

title: caramel clusters
directions: Stir butter or margarine, caramels and milk over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add chopped nuts, coconut and corn flakes.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls down in pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Mix and spread cream cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and Ranch mix.
Top with diced veggies:
red pepper, green pepper, onions, broccoli, carrots or your favorite.

title: stuffed french bread(prep time:  15 minutes)
directions: Slice the bread lengthwise and remove inside dough. Combine all remaining ingredients and mix well. Fill the hollowed bread with the mixture. Re-assemble the loaf. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 3 hours or until ready to serve. Slice the loaf in 1-inch sections and serve. Serves 12.

title: danny's chili
directions: Cook ground beef with green pepper and onion.
Add chili block and mix together in large pan.
Add water.
Add chili with beans and canned tomatoes. Cook slowly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Let cream cheese reach room temperature.
(May use microwave.) Mix lime jello (dry) with cream cheese.
Add 1 cup boiling water; dissolve cheese mix completely.
Add pineapple and pecans. Refrigerate.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and milk in double boiler until thick. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Stir until well blended; pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with a little cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn curry
directions: Combine margarine, vegetables and curry powder in a skillet. Cook over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in sour cream and pepper.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often; do not allow to boil.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken with plums
directions: Skin chicken. Coat with flour.
Brown chicken in a skillet. Place in a baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix sugar and graham crackers; add melted butter.
Mix well. Pat on sides and in bottoms of deep dish pie shell and bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: ham balls
directions: Shape ham loaf into balls.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven. Baste with the mixture of pineapple, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hobo stew
directions: Mix all and heat.
Eat with crumbled Doritos.

title: chicken breasts with angel hair pasta
directions: In small bowl, whisk together salad dressing and mustard; set aside.
In medium skillet, saute chicken in butter until browned; transfer to dish.
Keep warm.
Pour wine into skillet; cook over medium-high heat, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of skillet, about 5 minutes.
Whisk in dressing mixture; blend well. Serve chicken with sauce over pasta; sprinkle with parsley.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cut fruit and nuts into pieces (half cherry size); coat with flour and set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside. Cream softened butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and extracts. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add sifted flour and egg whites; mix well.
Pour over floured fruit and nuts and mix until all of fruit mixture is well covered.
Spoon into well-greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Put a pan of water on rack below cake for last hour of baking time.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese and margarine over low heat.
Add soup and onion; stir until smooth.
Mix with potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: english toffee
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Mix cocoa in well.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Fold in beaten egg whites and add nuts.
Butter pan and spread layer of vanilla wafer crumbs on bottom.
Pour in half of mixture by spoonfuls so it can be spread evenly over crumbs; add another layer of crumbs.
Add rest of mixture and sprinkle top with remainder of crumbs.
Let set in refrigerator 24 hours. Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: savory rice pilaf
directions: In 2-quart pan, combine the rice and oil.
Stir over medium heat until rice is golden brown (5 minutes).
Add stock, apple juice, onion, garlic, lemon juice and thyme.
Reduce heat to low; cover pan and simmer until all liquid has been absorbed and rice is tender, about 20 minutes.
Fluff with fork before serving. Serves 6.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Add butter to water; bring to rolling boil. Stir in flour vigorously over low heat.
Beat 1 minute until mixture forms a ball.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until smooth. Drop 1/4 cup of the mixture onto ungreased cookie sheet, spacing 3 inches apart.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; keep away from drafts.
Allow to cool.

title: carrot-stuffed patty pan squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blanch the squash whole in boiling water for 5 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain and plunge into cold water to stop the cooking.
Drain again.
Cut off the stem end of squash, scoop out a small amount of pulp and discard.
Melt the butter in large saute pan and saute the onion for 2 minutes. Add parsley, carrots, garlic and water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until water evaporates.
Add the herbs, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Heat until cheese melts.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Spoon the filling into the squash on a baking sheet and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through. Yield: 6 servings.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Peel, dice and cook potatoes for 8 minutes.
Cut cheese into small chunks.
Mix together all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place oleo in baking dish and place in oven to melt.
Put blueberries and 1 cup sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil.
In meantime, mix remaining 1 cup sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour this mixture over melted butter.
Do not stir! Pour hot berries over flour mixture.
Do not stir!
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: mrs. dash chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry. Spread with mayonnaise and sprinkle with Mrs. Dash seasoning. Place chicken in baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: crab soup
directions: Simmer vegetables in chicken broth 30 minutes.
Add tomato paste and seasoning.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove cartilage and shell from crabmeat.
Stir in soup.
Heat and serve.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Wash and drain chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the cranberry sauce, dressing and onion soup and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste during baking time. Serve with rice.

title: fig squares
directions: Bake in 9-inch square pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with powdered sugar.

title: roast beef
directions: Bake meat, water and beef cubes for 4 hours at 300°.
Add vegetables and cook 3 more hours at 250°.
Meat is very tender and delicious.

title: ambrosia bowl
directions: Peel oranges; remove white membrane.
Cut oranges crosswise into 1/8 inch thick slices.
Drain pineapple, saving syrup. Combine syrup and Cointreau; set aside.
Peel bananas. Cut diagonally into 1/8 inch thick slices.
In attractive serving bowl, layer half the orange slices; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Layer half the banana slices and half the pineapple chunks. Sprinkle with half the coconut.
Repeat layers of fruit and sugar.
Pour syrup mixture over fruit; sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Decorate with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate several hours, until well chilled.
Makes 10 servings.

title: zucchini with cheese
directions: Cut bacon and fry until brown.
Add sliced zucchini and onion. Add enough water to cover zucchini.
Add tomato sauce and cook until zucchini is tender.
Just before serving, lay cheese over vegetables and cover until melted and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Whip eggs; add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish with Pam.
Arrange potatoes and add onions.
Crumble bacon.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with sliced butter, salt and pepper.
Cover foil and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: mountain rum butter
directions: Mix ingredients with even consistency.
Let cool.
Dust top decoratively with powdered sugar.
Serve with plum pudding, mince meat pies or brown bread.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Boil eggs. Set aside. Peel. Divide sausage roll into 4 pieces.
Roll out 1 sausage piece on floured board.
Place egg in center of sausage meat and mold to egg until egg is encased in sausage meat. Brush sausage egg with egg wash and roll in bread crumbs.
Deep-fry sausage egg rolls in hot oil until deep brown in color.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Saute onions, green peppers, celery and mushrooms in melted butter until lightly browned.
Add flour, salt and pepper and mix well.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk, then water and cook until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Arrange layers of salmon, peas, white sauce and potato chips in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with layer of potato chips and dot with butter. Cover and bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer or until top is brown.

title: chinese style fried rice
directions: In a small saucepan, bring 1 1/4 c water to a boil.
Stir in rice and remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Meanwhile using a 10 in skillet, cook egg (slightly beaten) in 3 Tbsp, butter.
Add 1/3 c chopped onion and the rice.
Saute, stirring over medium heat until mixture slightly browned.
Mix 1/4 c water with 2 to 3 Tbsp soy sauce and stir into the rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake with mix.
Crumble one of the layers in the bottom of a punch bowl.
Mix pudding; when set, spread it over the cake. Drain pineapple and spread over pudding.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over this.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over this and repeat the layers again.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Add egg yolks and add soda to buttermilk.
Add flour and milk, alternating.
Add vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake in 3 layers at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler over hot water.
Add corn syrup and rum.
Combine crushed vanilla wafer crumbs, powdered sugar and chopped pecans.
Add to the chocolate mix and mix well.
Cover and let stand for 30 minutes.
Make 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar.
Place in tight container to "ripen" for 3 to 4 days.
Be sure to keep tightly covered.

title: family favorite chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, sugar and salt. Gradually add egg yolks and milk. Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until thickened. Filling will be slightly lumpy. Add vanilla and butter and beat with an electric mixer until smooth. Cool until lukewarm and pour into a baked pie shell. If you choose, you may top with meringue and bake until brown, or you may chill the pie and top with whipped cream.

title: dijon chicken with double cheese bake(can do the day before and just bake the day of the brunch!)
directions: In greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, place bread. Layer with chicken, mushrooms and cheeses. Meanwhile in large bowl, whisk remaining ingredients. Pour over layered chicken mixture. Cover; refrigerate 6 hours or overnight. Heat oven to 325°. Uncover; bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until set in center. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: strawberry dumplins
directions: Bring 1st 2 sugars and water to boil, reduce heat - simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and pour over berries in a casserole dish.
Combine other ingredients as making biscuits, drop over berries.
Sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. sugar. Bake @ 450 for 25 - 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring everything except corn and baking soda to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda; blend and pour over corn.
Mix well.
Spread lightly on 2 large cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Fry onion, oregano and hamburger.
Pour off grease.
Add sauce and paste to hamburger. Layer bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with cooked noodles.
Sprinkle with cheeses and hamburger mix.
Beginning with noodles, repeat. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes (until bubbly).

title: brownies
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and stir until blended.
Turn into a slightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into 16 (2-inch) squares while warm.
Yield:
16 (2-inch) squares.

title: fried potato cakes
directions: Combine potatoes, flour, egg, milk and onion in bowl; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil in skillet.
Brown on both sides, pressing with spatula to flatten.
Yields 12 cakes.

title: dannon fat-free muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Gently stir in yogurt and milk, blending just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill lightly greased or paper lined muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or until browned.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: ginger molasses cookies
directions: Combine flour, ginger, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
With an electric mixer set at medium low speed, beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Reduce speed to low and gradually beat in flour mixture until just incorporated.
Chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until edges just start to brown, about 15 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet 2 minutes before removing to racks. Cool completely.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: almond raisin cake
directions: Cream shortening and
sugar.
Add
beaten egg yolks. Sift together flour,
baking
powder
and
salt.
Add raisins. Mix together, adding 1 cup
milk
and the extracts.
Fold in 2 egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Bake in tube pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: drunken dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer with hot dogs (regular) cut up for one hour.

title: baked chicken(low cholesterol)
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Dip into margarine, then roll in cracker crumbs. Place in a pan at 350° for an hour or until done. Serves 4.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients with nuts.
Add bananas.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Simmer chicken in salt and water for 20 minutes.
Shred breasts.
In skillet, melt margarine, sour cream, Ro-Tel, soup, onion and half of cheese.
Dip tortillas in mixture until one side is covered.
Stuff with chicken, onion, olives and more cheese. Fold and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour leftover mixture over stuffed tortillas.
Add remainder of cheese over top.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ethel's dish
directions: Mix pineapple, fruit cocktail and pudding in a bowl.
Add marshmallows; mix well, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: quick pumpkin pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk in large bowl.
Refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Then add pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice.
Mix well.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Refrigerate at 10 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sparerib combination
directions: Cut ribs in serving pieces.
Season with salt and pepper. Bake in oven until almost done.
Remove from oven; add onions. Pour sauce and tomato sauce over ribs; add potatoes.
Cook at 350° in oven until done completely.

title: blender coconut custard pie
directions: In
a blender, combine all ingredients (except coconut) and blend
for	3 minutes.
Spray a large pie plate with Pam. Pour mixture into plate and allow to set.
Sprinkle coconut on top. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.

title: mary's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the first 2 ingredients.
Mix in the egg, vanilla and almond. Mix together the flour, soda and cream of tartar, add to creamed mixture.
Refrigerate 2-3 hours.
Heat oven to 375.
Roll dough out and cut into shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet for 7-8 minutes.
These are my favorite sugar cookies.

title: sopa de piscado(fish soup)
directions: Heat oil and saute onion, garlic, celery, cilantro and green chile.
When vegetables are clear, add fish and stir-fry with vegetables.
Add 1/2 glass of water or enough to make soupy. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
This soup is quick and hearty but very spicy.

title: parmesan bread
directions: Brush 1 side of each slice of French bread with melted margarine or butter.
Sprinkle buttered sides of bread with Italian seasoning, then with Parmesan cheese.
Place bread slices, cheese side up, on the unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from the heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is golden and bubbly.
Makes 8 slices.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with black pepper, garlic salt and a few dots of butter.
Add mushroom soup and place French onion rings on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Spread chocolate chips in bottom of pie shell.
Stir together butter, sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, and pour over chips.
Add pecans, pushing them down in the filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can add a tablespoon of bourbon, if desired.

title: cheese buds
directions: With mixer, blend cheese and butter.
Sift flour and pepper. Gradually work into cream mixture with spoon.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 1-inch rounds.
Brush with egg white; top with pecans.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in hot oven preheated to 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Fill greased pie plate with apples.
Sprinkle apples with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Combine remaining ingredients in mixing bowl and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water with salt for 3 minutes. Add margarine and cheese and then eggs. Mix well and pour into a greased baking dish. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Top with Parmesan cheese and paprika. Let sit for a few minutes and cut into servings or spoon out. Serves 6 to 7 people.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Stir in whipping cream, then rhubarb.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Spread topping on and bake 15 minutes more at 400°.

title: fruit nut cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add flour and milk, 1/2 at a time, then add remaining ingredients and mix well. Prepare Bundt pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
When cool, ice with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Mix all together; cook 10 or 15 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together into a well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Make 3 indentations in mixture.
In one put 1 teaspoon vinegar.
Put vanilla in the second and in the third put oil.
Over all, pour 1 cup cold water and stir until blended. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: cowpoke beans
directions: Wash and pick over beans; put in mixing bowl.
Cover beans with cold water and soak overnight.
Next morning, put beans and water into Dutch oven and bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and simmer 3 hours or until tender.
Add more water if necessary.
Serves 8.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Melt butter; add mustard, poppy seed and onion.
Slice each roll with electric knife.
Remove top and spread both sides with butter mixture.
Combine ham and cheese and place on roll bottoms, then cover with tops.
Bake in roll foil container for 10 to 15 minutes in 400° oven.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add oil; mix.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice; add to egg mixture gradually.
Fold in apples, nuts and dates.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° (depending on your oven).
Cook in tube pan; good with whipped cream.

title: tangy grilled beef
directions: Mix soup, sugar, lemon juice, oil, Worcestershire, garlic powder & thyme. Place steak on lightly oiled grill rack over medium- hot coals. Grill uncovered to desired doneness (allow 15 minutes for medium), turning once & brushing often with soup mixture. Heat remaining soup mixture to a boil & serve with steak.

title: pizzelle(italian waffles)
directions: These are made with electric pizzelle iron.

title: christmas date balls
directions: Blend in saucepan and cook over medium heat the first 4 ingredients . Stir constantly.
Cook for 10 minutes or until mixture is well away from sides of pan.
Remove from heat and add the Rice Krispies, pecans and vanilla.
Make into balls and roll in coconut or chopped nuts.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Cook until thick; take off stove.
Add butter and stir until smooth.
Pour in pie shell. Beat egg whites.
Add 6 tablespoons, two at a time.
Put on pie and brown.

title: white bread
directions: This makes 4 loaves.
Bake at 325°
for 35 to 40 minutes. Dissolve yeast and 2 teaspoons sugar in warm water.
Set aside for 10 minutes.
Mix hot water, shortening, salt and sugar in large mixer bowl; add milk.
Add 2 cups flour to make sure the mixture is cool enough to add the yeast.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead a few minutes.
Let rise twice, then work out in loaves.
Let rise and bake.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat; drain.
Mix meat with spaghetti sauce; cook until hot.
Pour into casserole dish.
Layer with sour cream, then Cheddar cheese.
Put rolls on top and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easter bunny salad
directions: Put a lettuce
leaf on a plate.
Put a peeled pear half upside-down on the
leaf.
Add
2 cloves for eyes and 2 almond halves for ears.
Add 1 teaspoon cottage cheese for a tail.

title: mom's potato wedges
directions: Scrub unpeeled potatoes well.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise.
Then cut into even wedges.
Boil potato wedges for 5 minutes in salted water; drain and pat dry.
Spread wedges in a single layer on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Brush with oil; sprinkle on spices and herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown and cheeses are melted.
Serve as snack or with any meat dish.

title: taco salad
directions: Place the jello, pudding mix and water in a large saucepan and stir. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Mixture will become thickened and transparent. Chill just until set, about 4 hours.
Beat in the Cool Whip and stir in the mandarin oranges.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger first.
Let cool, then combine all and toss with dressing.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a pan.
Add oil, water and food coloring.
Stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.
When it sticks together in a ball and seems cooked through, turn out onto a table and knead at once for at least 5 minutes.
Store in a tight container.
Do not refrigerate.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Mix soup, cheese, mayonnaise and onion flakes. Blend in eggs.
Toss lightly with drained broccoli.

title: quick and easy bucket cake
directions: You will also need a 1 gallon clear plastic bucket.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Place shrimp in a shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with seasoning and lemon juice. Dot with butter. Broil on one side for 3 minutes; turn and broil for 3 minutes more. Serve with toast or garlic bread.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Mix sugar with cornstarch and add to egg.
When well mixed, add 1/2 cup of liquid from pineapple and cook (low heat) over hot water until thickened.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup of crushed pineapple and set aside to chill, then add 1/3 cup heavy cream and vanilla.
Serve in sherbet glasses.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter. Add cereal and mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: meltaway cookies
directions: Mix the cornstarch, powdered sugar and flour.
Cut in the oleo.
To make a soft dough, add almond and/or vanilla.
Shape in small balls; roll in sugar.
Place on baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass or cookie stamps.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan.
Remove from stove. Add rest of the ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: orangy fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Chill.
Serve over fruit compotes or fruit kabobs.

title: yummy fudge
directions: Place butter in pan, heat until melted.
Add sugar and cream; blend well.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes until soft ball stage.
Add semi-sweet morsels, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in buttered pan.
Mix well
and chill.

title: chicken chutney salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir well.
Combine remaining ingredients and toss with dressing.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with sugar, Cool Whip and peanut butter.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate; let cool for 2 or 3 hours before serving.
(You may use a baked crust, if you wish.)

title: zucchini jam
directions: Boil zucchini until clear.
Do not add water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Boil for 6 minutes and remove from heat.
Add peach and apricot jellos.
Stir until dissolved.
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into Jell-O in large bowl until dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes until mixture will mound. Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into 6 cup mold.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: orange sponge cake
directions: Combine flour and 1/3 cup sugar; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Add orange peel and juice; beat until very thick.
Gradually add 2/3 cup sugar and salt, beating constantly.
Sift flour mixture over egg yolk mixture a little at a time, folding just until blended.
Wash beaters.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Thoroughly fold yolk mixture into whites.
Bake in ungreased 10-inch tube pan at 325° for about 55 minutes.
Invert cake in pan to cool.

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: Add onion, rice and beef.
Stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly and simmer 25 minutes.

title: beef brisket
directions: Put beef in 9 x 9-inch pan, fat side down.
Add seasonings to taste, cover with foil.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Test; cook longer if needed.

title: three in one dip
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Refrigerate. Serve cold or hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together.
Grease loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and has hollow sound when thumped.

title: hominy ole
directions: Brown bacon and onion; add hominy.
Saute a few minutes. Drain off excess grease.
Blend in tomatoes, taco seasoning mix, cheese and Tabasco sauce.
Heat thoroughly, stirring until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: roasted red pepper and artichoke dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing mix and spread on tray or plate.
Layer red peppers over this, then artichokes over peppers. Chill and serve.

title: toffee
directions: Combine ingredients in a small, heavy saucepan.
Boil up, stirring constantly.
Boil up several times until mixture nearly burns.
Immediately pour into molds, i.e. ice cube trays or candy/lollipop molds.
Soak the empty saucepan in hot, soapy water.
Pick the hardened toffee out of the molds (around edges) and cool.
Add flavors/spices: orange/tangerine pulp, half margarine/half peanut butter, etc.
If liquified, boil over extra or you'll get caramel instead of hard candy.

title: baked macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, alternate macaroni in 2 layers with 2 cups of cheese in layers; set aside.
Prepare sauce by melting butter in medium saucepan; remove from heat.
Blend in flour; gradually stir in milk, then seasonings.
Pour sauce over macaroni.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and brown.

title: crab dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese; stir in remaining ingredients except green onions.
Mix well.
Stir in green onions.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: icing for cakes
directions: Put 1/2 box sugar in bowl.
Add water and shortening.
Blend on slow.
Add vanilla, salt and rest of sugar.
Blend until smooth.
This recipe will frost a 9 x 13-inch cake, sides and top.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place the ground beef in the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch square baking dish.
Mix the undiluted soups together and place over ground beef.
Place Tater Tots over this mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: diet punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except 7-Up.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 7-Up just before serving.
Yields about 50 servings.

title: simply pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven, brown roast on medium heat.
Add onion soup mix, blended with water.
Simmer, covered, turning occasionally, 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Stir in oats and peanut butter.
Drop with spoon on wax paper.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Place butter in 9-inch round (8-inch square) baking dish. Microwave on full power for 30 seconds or until melted.
Stir in brown sugar and spread evenly in dish.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Arrange pineapple slices over sugar-butter mixture.
Place cherry in center of each pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts over pineapple slices.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions using juice for liquid.
Pour batter over pineapple slices.
Microwave at 30% power for 7 minutes, rotate pan.
Microwave at full power for 3 to 4 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 1 minute on flat surface.
Turn out onto platter and serve warm or cool.

title: oriental ribs
directions: Put ribs in crock-pot.
Mix all other ingredients together and puree in blender.
Pour sauce over ribs and cook until done. Remove ribs and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over this and cook at 400° until brown.
Baste often with sauce from the pan.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour 1 cup at a time. Refrigerate for a while. Put on wax paper and roll out. Bake at 375°.

title: captain's casserole
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients in saucepan until cheese is melted. Combine rice, oregano and pepper in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Drain tomatoes, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Stir into rice with 1 cup water.
Slice tomatoes; reserve several for garnish. Arrange tomatoes over rice.
Add onion, tuna and olives.
Pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with chips.
Arrange tomatoes on top. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg and water together.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and onions together.
Roll chicken in flour, dip in egg wash and then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes.
Top with sliced cheese (turn chicken after 20 minutes).
Bake until cheese is melted slightly.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together all ingredients (except chips and nuts) at lowest speed.
Then beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into pan; sprinkle on toppings of chips and nuts and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Cool; lightly toss rice with remaining ingredients in large bowl, using 1/2 cup dressing. Chill.
Just before serving, toss with remaining dressing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls on pizza pan (put points to center).
Pat together good.
Brown sausage and drain.
Spread over rolls.
Fry hash browns in sausage pan just until thawed.
Sprinkle over sausage on crescent rolls.
Sprinkle onion, green pepper and cheese over potatoes.
Beat eggs, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese; pour over the ingredients in pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all together and spoon in muffin tin about half full. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6.

title: orange loaf cake
directions: Sift together into bowl the cake flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add shortening and orange juice. Beat 2 minutes and add eggs, beating after each one.
Bake in loaf pan 60 to 65 minutes at 350°.

title: company hamburger casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Add ground beef to rice, then add soy sauce, mushrooms and soups.
Mix well and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; bake 1 hour.
May top with buttered bread crumbs or 1/2 cup slivered almonds.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel candy
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, 1 cup half and half, syrup and butter.
Cook over medium heat until it comes to a rolling boil (7 to 8 minutes).
Add remaining half and half until 245° on candy thermometer or dropped in ice water forms a ball (35 or 40 minutes).
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cover and refrigerate.
Cut into squares.
Melt chocolate; place 1 or 1 1/2 teaspoons of chocolate on each square.
Place pecans onto chocolate and refrigerate.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Put chocolate in saucepan.
Cover with 2 inches very hot tap water.
Cover.
Let stand 5 minutes or until chocolate is soft enough to stick toothpick through.
When chocolate is soft, but not dissolved, drain water.
Do not worry that some water clings.
Add yolks.
Stir with whisk and cook until thick.
Remove from heat. Add butter, salt and vanilla.
Mix well and cool.
Beat egg whites; gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Mix into chocolate. Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip-oatmeal-walnut brownies(a cross between oatmeal cookies and brownies.)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch rectangular pan. Prepare fudge-like brownies as directed, except stir chocolate chips and oats into batter.
Spread in pan. Bake 25 to 27 minutes. Cool completely for easier cutting. Store tightly covered.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place sugar and cinnamon into a plastic bowl with a lid. Shake until mixed thoroughly.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces. Put one can of biscuits at a time into plastic bowl.
Cover mixture.
Take biscuits out and place into a greased Bundt pan. Repeat with remaining 2 cans biscuits.
Melt 1 stick butter and mix with remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Pour over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Invert on a plate and allow butter to drizzle over cooked bread.

title: scalloped eggplant italian
directions: Dip eggplant into beaten egg then into crumbs.
Brown in hot oil.
Place 1/4 of the eggplant slices in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole and top with 1/4 of the cheese slices.
Combine the tomato sauce with the remaining ingredients and spoon 1/4 of the sauce over the eggplant and cheese.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, ending with sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a dish, slightly buttered, for 25 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat sugar and butter until fluffy. Blend in water, egg and vanilla. Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Heat oven to 350°.
Spoon out on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 14
minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: In a 2-quart microwavable dish, melt margarine.
Add brown sugar, salt and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil in microwave and boil on full power for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in soda.
Stir well.
Spray paper grocery bag with cooking spray. Pour in popcorn and pour syrup over popcorn.
Close bag and shake. Microwave in bag on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake again and microwave for another 1 1/2 minutes; cool.
Stir while cooling in large bowl.
Serves many.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt together in saucepan butter and cocoa.
Remove from heat. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake exactly 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: snack pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Grease cookie sheet with spray Mazola. Place biscuits on cookie sheet.
Flatten each biscuit with the bottom of a glass, leaving a rim.
Dip glass in flour to prevent sticking, starting from the center of each biscuit.
Use your fingers to push out dough to make it bigger.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: In greased casserole, layer bread pieces in large casserole dish.
Add the sausage and cheese; add milk, mustard and salt and pour over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: velvety chicken casserole
directions: Cook artichoke hearts according to package directions.
Cook mushrooms in margarine until tender.
Combine chicken, mushrooms and artichokes and place in buttered flat casserole.
Prepare gravy mix according to directions.
Remove from heat; add margarine and cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Stir in wine and pour over chicken mixture.
Combine melted margarine with crumbs and sprinkle over all.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Let cool and cut into bite size pieces and place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix soups and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Top with Ritz crackers and pats of butter.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: creamy shells with ham and broccoli
directions: Cook shells; drain.
Saute garlic in butter, then add ham and broccoli.
Cook until broccoli is crisp-tender, approximately 5 minutes.
Stir in cream.
Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes. Stir in cheese.
Lower heat and cook until cheese is melted.
Toss with shells.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together except about half of the catsup.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Pour remaining catsup over the top and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then fold in Cool Whip.
Chill several hours.

title: drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and sugar together until light and fluffy. Continue creaming while adding eggs slowly. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Drop small portions on greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Cook Grape-nuts in water until soft and mixture is thick (5 to 6 minutes).
Add to milk mixture.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Set in pan of water.
Bake until custard sets.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix baking powder, salt, soda and sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast.
Knead lightly; do not let rise.
Shape and bake immediately at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and add soup, tomatoes, beans, and American cheese. Line casserole dish with slightly crushed Doritos chips.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Fry chicken coated with flour. Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken. Cook until golden brown.
Mix rice, onions, peppers and soup.
Stir well.
Put in large casserole.
Stack chicken on top. Bake at 350° until all ingredients are cooked tender.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain grease.
Line the bottom of a casserole dish with Tater Tots.
Spoon meat and onion mixture on top.
Mix soups together and spread on top of meat.
Cook in a 350° oven for about 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Let melt.
Serve hot.
Serve with a green vegetable and your meal is complete.

title: pickled beets
directions: Pack beets in hot jars, filling within 1/2-inch to top.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to each jar.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over beets and seal.
Process in hot water bath 1/2 hour. Best if you wait 2 to 3 weeks before eating.
This makes 2 quarts.
Increase recipe as needed.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone (overnight in crock-pot). Place in large casserole dish.
Add veggies and shredded eggs. Mix soup and chicken broth; pour on top.
Add 1/2 cup more broth to keep from drying out.
Mix flour, milk and butter well; pour over chicken mixture.
Do not stir!
Cook at 400° until top browns, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Cream
butter;
add sugars, vanilla and egg.
Beat until light.
Add
sifted
dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill until firm enough to roll.
Halve dough and roll each half on floured waxed
paper.
Spread
with filling.
Roll up tightly from end. Wrap
in
wax paper.
Chill overnight.
Freeze for easier slicing. Slice
and bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove core from cabbage.
Place whole head in a pot with boiling water. cover, cook 3 minutes or until softened enough to pull off individual leaves.
Cut thick center stem from each leaf. Chop remaining cabbage.
Saute onion in butter; add meat, rice, eggs and Saptini; mix thoroughly.
Place a heaping tablespoon of meat mixture on each cabbage leaf.
Tuck sides over filling while rolling leaf around filling.
Place half the chopped cabbage on bottom of a large pot or Dutch oven or pan (oven).
Fill with layers of the cabbage rolls.
Cover with remaining chopped cabbage. Combine tomato soup and tomato sauce, mix until smooth.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve cabbage rolls with the sauce.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix salsa and cheese in crock-pot; heat until cheese melts. Brown hamburger meat in skillet; add to cheese and salsa.
Serve with chips.

title: chinese vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and put in greased casserole the Veg-All, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, cheese and mayonnaise. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Mix 1/2 bag of stuffing mix with 1/2 stick margarine; put on top of casserole after casserole has baked for 30 minutes. Return to oven and let crumbs brown.

title: deluxe chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt and pepper; stir well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to chicken mixture and toss lightly.

title: festive fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Excellent as salad.
Best as dessert.
Delicious served over vanilla ice cream.
Pretty for Christmas.

title: easy as pie pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze for 2 hours before serving.

title: pizza dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve.
Add 2 cups flour and the salt.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in remaining flour. Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in lightly greased bowl; turn dough over to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Turn onto board and knead enough to force out bubbles.
Divide in half. Roll each half out and stretch to fit an oiled 12-inch pizza pan. Top with favorite toppings and bake at 425°.
This recipe doubles and triples nicely to feed bigger crowds.

title: fat-free old fashioned spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in the ingredients one at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Pour batter into a 9 x 9-inch nonstick baking pan lightly coated with cooking spray and dusted with flour.
Bake 30 minutes.
Ice with Meringue Cream.
Fat-free serving size is 1/5 of cake.

title: aunt ola's canned grape juice
directions: Wash grapes and put in quart jar.
Add sugar and fill jar with boiling water.
Seal jar.
Let ripen at least 4 weeks before using.

title: salad
directions: Cut vegetables. Combine with mushrooms, olives and instant onion. Pour dressing over all and mix. Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion. Add sour cream and stir until thick. Add grated cheese. Fold in beans.
Pour in greased casserole. Add melted butter to crushed corn flakes and sprinkle on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°. Serves 6.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until barely tender.
Drain and mix together. Heat the remaining ingredients.
Pour over drained carrots and add 1 green pepper or onion, selected for color.
May add celery.
Let sit for 2 or 3 days. Keeps well.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with mixer until fluffy. Gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.

Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans or wire racks 10 minutes. Remove from pans.
Let cool completely on wire racks. Spread Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake. Store cake in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Drop 1 rounded tablespoonful of dough into ungreased muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
While hot, press one miniature Reese's peanut butter cup on each cookie.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook on low heat for 1 hour. Can be made ahead.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Blend olive oil and garlic in blender; coat potatoes.
Bake in single layer on 2 cookie sheets until golden, turning often (45 minutes to an hour).
Meanwhile blanch pea pods; drain (stems and strings removed).
Combine oil, vinegar, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Let potatoes cool slightly; toss with dressing, pea pods and tomatoes.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven
to
In large bowl, combine filling ingredients.
Mix well
and turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes;
reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut off tips of corn kernels into a large bowl.
Scrape milk and remaining pulp from cob with a paring knife.
Set aside.
Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving about 1/4 cup drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Add corn, butter and remaining ingredients to drippings in skillet.
Cook over medium heat 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Spoon corn mixture into a serving dish and sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Yields 12 servings.

title: stuffed flounder fillets
directions: Wash fillets; drain well on paper towels.
Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add shrimp, crab meat, bread crumbs, parsley and egg; mix.
Spread on fish fillets.
Roll up; place in lightly greased baking dish.
Pour white wine sauce over fillets.
Top with bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and additional chopped parsley. Refrigerate overnight at this point, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spudnuts(raised potato doughnuts)
directions: Scald milk. Add shortening, sugar and salt. When lukewarm, add the yeast which has been softened in warm water. Add the egg and the potatoes plus 1/2 cup water to the mixture.
Beat in the flour until the dough is stiff and leaves the side of the bowl.
Let rise until triple in bulk. Roll out about 1/3-inch thick and cut with a doughnut cutter.
Let rise on a floured board for 1 hour, then fry in hot grease.
Dip doughnuts in the following glaze.

title: quick hollandaise
directions: Place egg yolks in blender.
Blend with lemon juice, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper for 30 seconds. Add melted butter while blender is running (very slowly). If too runny, microwave 15 to 20 seconds and re-blend.
Repeat until desired thickness.

title: frozen mocha marbled loaf
directions: Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with foil. In a bowl, combine the cookie crumbs and butter. Press firmly onto the bottom and 1 1/2-inches up the sides of prepared pan. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until light. Add milk and vanilla; mix well. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon half of the mixture into another bowl and set aside. Dissolve coffee in hot water; fold into remaining cream cheese mixture. Fold in chocolate syrup. Spoon half of chocolate mixture over crust. Top with half of the reserved cream cheese mixture. Repeat layers. Cut
through layers with a knife to swirl the chocolate (pan will be full). Cover and freeze for 6 hours or overnight.

title: chili mac(30 minutes)
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in large skillet over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Stir in tomatoes, 1/4 cup A.1. sauce and chili powder.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium-low and simmer (covered) 10 minutes.
Stir chili into macaroni.
Garnish with green onions and cheese.
Makes four servings.

title: mom's chicken pie
directions: In a pan, cook the onion and cilantro (chopped).
Add the shredded chicken, peas and carrots, tomato sauce and the chicken broth.
Add 1/2 cup of water.
Mix and cook for approximately 30 minutes, until it gets a little juice.
Set aside.
Mix the baking powder and the flour.
Add the stick of butter.
Cutting it with a knife, cut it in until it gets very crumbly.
Knead the dough with your hands, until it is easy to handle and doesn't stick to your hands.
Roll it out and divide it in two.
Cover a pie plate with half of it.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes, or until light brown.
Set aside to cool.

title: graham cracker fruit cake
directions: Melt margarine, marshmallows and cherry juice in double boiler.
Pour over crushed graham crackers and other dry ingredients.
Mix well and pack in box (graham cracker box). Chill until firm.
Keep refrigerated.
Keeps for several months. I always chop the pecans.

title: waffles
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in large mixer bowl. Whip the eggs in small bowl; add milk and oil.
Mix well.
Beat into dry ingredients.
Makes four large waffles.

title: crockpot beef roast
directions: Put beef roast in bottom of crockpot.
Add mushroom soup, onion soup mix, and canned drink.
Cook on high 6 to 8 hours. Good over rice or potatoes.

title: yummy cukes
directions: Combine evaporated milk, Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Mix together until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until onion and cukes are well coated.
Chill before serving.

title: slush
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Combine and heat until boiling.
Stir constantly.
Pour over 3/4 head of grated cabbage.

title: mint sauce
directions: Place the mint in a pitcher or gravy boat and pour the boiling water over it.
Wait 20 minutes so that the mint has time to infuse the water.
Add sugar and wine or vinegar.
Stir well and serve.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Serve warm.
Best served with Triscuit crackers.

title: halloween mask paint
directions: Since I've not time to be,

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Salt and red pepper to taste.
Make into lunch balls.
Press onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: super bowl chili
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, brown beef and pork.
Drain off fat. Stir in undrained tomatoes, onions, green pepper, garlic, chili powder, sugar, red pepper, vinegar and cumin.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring frequently to avoid scorching.
To serve, ladle chili into soup bowls.
If desired, top each serving with shredded cheese and sour cream.
Makes 6 to 8 main dish servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Blend butter, flour and powdered sugar like pie crust and press in pie tin.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: "dam old chile"
directions: Ray Davis, the preacher's father, didn't care for chile like his mother and brother did, and she made it at least once a week. When a bowl was set before Ray, he would comment..."Dam Old Chile again!"

title: napoleans
directions: Thaw pastry per directions.
Preheat oven to 400°.
On floured surface, roll to 15 x 12-inches; cut lengthwise in thirds.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Prick with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir together cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and extract.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread 2 pastry sheets with cheese.
Stack. Top with remaining pastry.
Stir 1/2 cup sugar and milk in small bowl until smooth.
Spread over top.
Drizzle with chocolate. Chill.

title: cherry sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients in saucepan.
Pour over poultry of your choice.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Using a small Teflon skillet on top of stove on medium heat, melt 3 heaping tablespoonfuls butter.
Pour half of batter in skillet. cover with lid.
Keep check and when lightly brown, turn and brown other side.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil macaroni according to package directions.
Dilute soup with milk.
In a large casserole dish, put macaroni, tuna, soup mixture, salt and pepper and dry mustard.
Mix well.
(If needed, add more milk.)
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Cook approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: georgia peach pie
directions: Add and stir ingredients together.
Take half of the pie crust and put in bottom of a 10-inch pie pan.
Save the other half for top of pie.

title: double stuffed potatoes
directions: Rub potatoes with a drizzle of oil.
Place potatoes on a microwave safe plate and microwave on high for 12 minutes, rotating once.
While potatoes cook, add chopped bacon to hot skillet and brown until bits are crisp.
Add scallions and cook together with bacon one minute more. Drain bacon and scallions on paper towel.
Allow potatoes to cool enough to be handled.
Preheat broiler to high.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out flesh in a small bowl. Smash potato flesh together with sour cream until combined using potato masher. Stir in cheddar cheese, bacon and scallion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Scoop filling back into jackets of potatoes and place on a cookie sheet. Place potatoes in oven under broiler 6 inches from heat for 5 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until mixture thickens.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add favorite fruit, if desired.
Put into ice cream maker and churn until mixture hardens.

title: picking pork
directions: Trim ham, leaving small amount of fat for flavor during the cooking.
All skin and brine should be removed.
Rub the fresh ham with liberal amount of vinegar. Cover the ham completely with seasoned pepper, pressing the pepper into the sides so most of it will adhere.
Wrap in heavy duty foil tightly.
Place in roasting pan and bake in 200 degree over overnight or at least 10 hours. When unwrapped, the pork should fall apart or shred when pulled with a fork.
Place on a large serving platter on a buffet table and your guests will "pick" at it forever.
Serve with your favorite barbecue sauce.
Sounds too easy to be true or any good, but it is out of this world in flavor and taste.
Great for sandwiches.
Save the juices from the ham and cook rice in it for the best rice you will ever taste.
Everybody will love it.

title: chocolate chunk brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter a 9-inch baking pan.
Melt butter and let cool.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Chop chocolate squares, leaving some chunks as big as 1/2-inch.
With an electric mixer set at medium speed, beat the eggs and vanilla until frothy.
Gradually beat in the sugar, then the melted butter.
Reduce speed and beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chunks.
Pour batter into the prepared pan and smooth the top.
Bake until edges start to pull away from the sides of the pan, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Saute ground beef with onion in skillet until crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients, except crumbs.
Mix well.
Place in casserole; top with crumbs.
Bake at 359° for 1/2 hour.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add egg, one at a time, to sugar mixture.
Sift together the flour, salt and cocoa.
Add to cream mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add pecans or walnuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and make 12 rows of marshmallows on it.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Then top with frosting.

title: shirley's diabetic tea cakes
directions: Mix biscuit mix and fructose.
Add egg substitute and vanilla; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on vegetable-sprayed cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain can of sauerkraut, cut up.
Add chopped vegetables and sugar.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: california casserole
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan as follows:
1/2 stuffing (cooked according to package directions), 1 can mushroom soup, chicken chunks, vegetables, Cheez Whiz, remaining 1/2 of stuffing, 1 can mushroom soup.
Pour 3/4 cup water over all and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables.
Add sugar to mayonnaise.
Place grated cheese on top.
Top with 8 slices crumbled bacon or Bac*Os.
Let set in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours.

title: pineapple bar cake
directions: Mix granulated sugar and melted butter or oleo.
Beat eggs until foamy and mix with other ingredients.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add to mixture.
Add the drained crushed pineapple.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes or more.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Melt butter in pan, stirring in sugars.
Stir constantly until melted.
Pour mixture over soft ice cream in big bowl.
Mix well and store in refrigerator.
In a mug, pour 1 part mixture, 1 part rum and 2 parts boiling water.
Decorate with cinnamon stick and nutmeg.

title: hawaiian delight(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Combine mix, oil, pudding and eggs until well blended. Add 7-Up last and beat at medium speed until well blended (about 2 minutes). Do not overbeat. Grease and flour 3 cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until done.
Drain.
Season to taste. Set aside.
Fry tortillas in oil until flimsy.
Spoon hamburger and small amount of cheese in the tortilla.
Roll up and place side by side in a large casserole dish.
For sauce, take some flour, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Mix together.
Add water and tomato sauce.
This is an experimental process because it all depends on how large of a pan you are making.
The sauce needs to be thin enough and yet thick enough to have texture.
Pour over rolled-up enchiladas and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes, until all cheese is melted.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Top with topping made from lemon pudding and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and soda.
Add eggs and juice from fruit cocktail.
Mix until smooth and fold in fruit from fruit cocktail.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: martian pudding(pistachio salad)
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding mix together.
Add pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add cottage cheese.
Chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add onion, tomatoes, tomato paste, spaghetti mix and Italian seasoning to your taste.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Cook noodles and drain; rinse in cold water. Layer sauce, noodles and cheeses in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: fluffy cranberry salad
directions: Add sugar to berries and chill 2 hours. Fold in other ingredients. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach onion dip
directions: Blend all together.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Yield:
2 1/2 cups.
Serve in hollowed out bread loaf with vegetables and break chunks for dipping.

title: egg and mushroom soup
directions: Wash mushrooms and soak in a cup of hot water; set aside.
Beat eggs, set aside.
Boil chicken stock, add mushrooms with the water in which they were soaked.
Boiled 5 minutes.
Season with soy sauce, salt and Ajinomoto.
Stir in the cooking oil and beaten eggs.
Serve hot.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on the box in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or glass baking dish.
While cake is still hot, combine Eagle Brand milk and ice cream topping.
Pour over cake and let cool.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with Heath bar (grated) or Sensations.

title: quick pig in a blanket
directions: Chop cabbage into medium pieces.
Spread in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Heat tomato soup, paste and water to boiling and pour over other ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: waldorf cole slaw(yields 8 servings)
directions: Achiote is annatto seeds cooked in vegetable oil or olive oil. On the island they would cook the seeds in lard.
Annatto is the pulp of the tropical tree Bixa Orellana.
Annato dye is used in coloring some cheeses and in textiles and varnishes.
Caribbean and South American Indians use it for body paint.

title: nachos
directions: Cut each tortilla into 6 wedges.
Deep fry wedges in oil until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Paint each wedge with about 1 teaspoon refried beans.
Place on heatproof serving platter.
Top with shredded cheese.
Place in hot oven or under broiler just long enough to melt cheese.
Top each chip with 1 teaspoon of guacamole, then 1/2 teaspoon sour cream.
Place a few pieces of diced tomato on top.
Place more guacamole in center of platter. Serve with green and red chile sauce on the side.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger relish
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Mix all ingredients except spice bag and vinegar.
Boil 30 minutes in heavy pot.
Tie a string around the top of the spice bag.
Tie around handle and hang into vegetables. Cook until very thick.
Then add vinegar and boil on low until there is no free liquid.
Put into clean jars.
Leave headspace. Can be put in freezer.

title: four layer delight
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in a square cake pan; add flour and nuts. Mix and press in pan; bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add apples and nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Mix juice of 1 orange and 1 cup sugar. Spread on cake while hot.

title: marshmallow spiders
directions: Poke 8 pieces of 2-inch string licorice into each marshmallow end for legs.
Melt over low heat, 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Set spider of waxed paper and dribble a large spoonful of melted chocolate over marshmallow.
Add 2 M&M's for eyes.
Cool and eat.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed, garlic powder and onion powder. Spread this on the cooled crust. Top with chopped, raw vegetables of your choice.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order listed.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 2 pies.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a large bowl whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Bake sweet potatoes at 400° until soft, about 1 hour.
Let potatoes cool, remove skins and mash with butter.
