Add milk, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in beaten egg whites, fold in nuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes in a greased casserole dish or pan.
Top with marshmallows and broil until marshmallows brown.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar, lemonade, and pineapple juice.
Freeze for at least 12 hours.
Add 7-Up before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces (scissors work really well). Put white sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon into a paper sandwich bag.
Grease 10-inch or larger tube pan.
Shake the biscuit pieces, a few at a time, in the sugar and cinnamon; transfer to tube pan.

title: carrot soup(serves 4)
directions: Simmer all ingredients except cream until vegetables are done. Add cream just before serving; heat.

title: idiot bars
directions: Place crackers in jelly roll pan (ungreased), split and scored.
Boil butter
and
sugar
together	for 2 minutes; add pecans.
Spoon over crackers and bake 10 minutes in 350° oven. Cut and separate as soon as possible and put on rack to cool.

title: best bean salad
directions: Bring sugar, water and vinegar to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain all canned vegetables.
Place all vegetables in a large covered bowl and pour dressing over it.
Refrigerate overnight.
This will keep for 2 or 3 weeks.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Place in 9 x 13, greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: favorite meat loaf(microwave)
directions: In small bowl, combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard; set aside.
In large bowl, combine eggs, onion, crackers, ground beef, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup tomato sauce mixture; stir thoroughly.
Place meat mixture in glass ring mold or 2-quart microproof round casserole.
Put a microproof glass in center of meat mixture, bottom side up.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat.
Cook, uncovered, on High (maximum power) for 12 to 14 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together with a spoon or mixer.
Add next 3 ingredients, then add oats and pecans.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet, about a teaspoon for each cookie.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool and store in a tin to keep them crisp.

title: grandmother's tea cakes
directions: Beat softened margarine until fluffy.
Add sugar and continue beating.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add with vanilla.
This well form a soft dough. Divide cookie dough and roll out very thin on floured board.
Cut out and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° until brown.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Mix well and cook in 2 (9-inch) pans for 25 minutes at 375°. (Or may use cake mix.)

title: buttermilk dumplings
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift 3 times with baking powder, soda and salt. Add buttermilk and mix lightly with fork. Turn out on a floured board. Knead lightly 4 or 5 times and roll to 1/2-inch thick. Cut into rectangles, 1 x 3-inches, with floured knife. Drop into boiling chicken broth. Cover and boil gently for 12 minutes. Do not uncover during cooking. Serve immediately.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add chips and nuts.
Mix well to distribute evenly through.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the first 4 ingredients.
Remove and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: fried rice
directions: Cover rice with water and put lid on pan.
Put on medium heat until pan lid is hot.
Turn heat down to very low.
No salt.
Cook for 35 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Cool with lid off.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift all dry ingredients into large bowl.
Mix in shortening with pastry blender.
Add milk, then yeast mixture.
Stir until thoroughly moistened.
Turn onto floured board and knead a minute or two (no rising is required). Roll to desired thickness (1/2 inch is recommended) and cut into rounds.
Brush with melted butter and bake on ungreased pan at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Baked biscuits freeze well.

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine vegetables.
Heat sugar and vinegar on low heat until syrupy. Add mayonnaise, salt, pepper and syrup to vegetables.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill for 1 hour or more before serving.

title: crumb cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Add Crisco; mix well.
Remove 1/2 cup of crumb mixture and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients to rest of crumb mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased pan. Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: santa's punch
directions: Pour orange juice, pineapple and water in blender. On low speed, add ice cubes, one at a time, until all ice is crushed. Add cherries; blend all ingredients well and serve immediately.

title: maple-sugared pears
directions: Combine pear juice, brown sugar and oil in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice, maple syrup and cinnamon.
Arrange pear halves, cut side up, in a small, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Pour brown sugar mixture over pears and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rascals(spitzbuben)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and shortening as for pie dough. Add juice and grated rind of lemon and whole eggs and mix well.
Roll out 1/2 of the dough to fit the bottom of a 12 x 18 x 1-inch greased cookie sheet.
Spread a generous amount of good marmalade on the dough. Red raspberry and orange are very good.
Roll out and use the other half of the dough to form lattice decoration for top.
Bake in a slow oven at 350° for about 45 minutes. Cut into 2-inch squares or diamond shaped pieces.

title: pie crust(makes 1 crust)
directions: Mix together in a soft ball.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.

title: baked pineapple(easy rv recipe)
directions: Melt butter; add eggs.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a buttered 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until slightly browned and set.

title: harvest popcorn
directions: In a large pan, mix popped corn, shoestring potatoes and nuts. Melt the oleo and add all seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour over popcorn mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes, stirring once.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar, vanilla and orange rind.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder; add alternately with milk.
Pour batter into prepared 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: south-of-the-border soup
directions: Heat all together and garnish each serving with shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: fresh corn pancakes
directions: With a sharp knife, cut kernels from corn.
With back of a knife, scrape cobs to release milky pulp.
Make at least 2 cups. In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and pepper.
In a small bowl, beat together eggs, milk and cooking oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring only until flour is moistened.
Stir in corn.
Cook in hot oil, 2 tablespoons batter for each pancake.
Makes 24 pancakes.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, sugar and oil and let set at least two hours. Add egg, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well and drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Cream the cream cheese, sugar and melted margarine. Spread over cake mix. Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pizza
directions: Flatten biscuits and place apple slices on top.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and dot with butter.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: russian tea
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, water, cinnamon and cloves; bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add tea, remove from heat and let stand, covered for 5 minutes.
Strain; add remaining ingredients.
Heat but do not boil.
Serve hot.
Yields about 8 cups.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: In large bowl mix pudding and 3 cups milk, then mix in Cool Whip.
In a 13 x 9-inch glass dish lay only enough graham crackers out to cover entire bottom, then pour 1/2 of the pudding mixture on top of crackers and smooth out.
Put another layer of graham crackers, then pour the rest of pudding mixture on top and spread out.
Put another layer of graham crackers.
Mix 3 tablespoons milk into frosting in canister.
Pour out onto top of crackers and spread out.
Chill for at least 12 hours.

title: old fashion lettuce salad
directions: Chop bacon strips and fry in skillet, add vinegar and water and bring to boiling.
Sprinkle salt and sugar on lettuce and pour boiling mixture over the lettuce.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Mix apples and pecans with 1 cup of flour and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs together.
Combine dough mixture with fruit.
Pour into tube cake pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: snowballs(for christmas)
directions: Mix whipping cream and sugar until soft peaks form.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Stack three or four vanilla wafers together. Cover each stack with whipped cream mixture.
Cut cherries in half and place one on each snowball.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sweetheart punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale and ice cream in a large covered pitcher. Chill until ready to serve. Pour into bowl and add ginger ale. Float vanilla ice cream on top and serve.

title: the absolutely best peach pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; add water and peaches. Bring to a boil for one minute. Cool. Add bourbon, lemon or sherry. Pour into a pastry-lined 9-inch pie dish. Make crisscross on top. Bake at 400° to 425° for about 30 minutes. Serve alone or with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: avgolemono soup(egg lemon rice)
directions: Cook rice
in
chicken	broth
until tender.
Turn down heat. Beat
eggs and combine with lemon juice and cornstarch, adding 2 cups
hot
water
and
mix	well.
Slowly add the egg mixture to the soup, vigorously stirring with a wire whip for 2 minutes. Turn heat off.
Use whole grain rice (Uncle Ben's) or parboil rice.

title: toothpick appetizers(makes 12 servings)
directions: While potato is still hot, cut into 24 cubes.
Sprinkle with wine and salt and pepper; set aside.
Cut herring and mushrooms into quarters.
Cut lox, white fish and red or green pepper into 24 pieces.
Cut cherry tomatoes and artichoke hearts in half.
Cut cucumber into 6 (3/4-inch) pieces, then into quarters.
Cut baby corns into 12 pieces.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle, in layers, the nuts, chocolate bits, butterscotch chips and coconut over the crust.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut in squares.
Delicious.

title: west virginia reunion beans
directions: Brown sausage.
Saute onion and pepper.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: delicious rolls
directions: Mix together the shortening, sugar and 1 cup boiling water, then cool.
When cool, add 1 cup cold water and eggs.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water and add.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Place in greased bowl and let rise.
Work down and make into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: sausage pilaf
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add celery, onion and green pepper; cook until tender, not brown.
Stir in pimiento, soup, milk, rice and seasonings.
Pour into an ungreased casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes, stirring occasionally with a fork. For topping, combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle evenly over the top and bake uncovered 20 more minutes.

title: walnut pineapple squares
directions: Mix ingredients together until dough leaves bowl clean. Refrigerate for about 3 hours.
Roll in granulated or powdered sugar; cut into squares, fill
and	roll.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute beef and onion.
Drain.
Combine with other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on heated hamburger buns.

title: cauliflower-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower and broccoli.
Heat soups and cheese.
Drain vegetables.
Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Add onion rings last 5 minutes or microwave 10 minutes on High.
Add onions and serve.

title: kartoffelsalat mit wurst(potato salad with sausages)
directions: Cook potatoes; peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Cook bacon until crisp; set aside.
Cook onion in bacon drippings.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except sausage.
Bring to boil.
Add bacon and pour over warm potato slices; gently toss.
Serve with sausages.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix milk and flour. Cook until thickened. Add soup and cheese. Stir until cheese melts. Add chicken. Pour over cooked spaghetti. Mix well. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: baker's chocolate one-bowl brownie recipe
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl at High for 2 minutes, or until melted.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Stir in sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes (do not overbake).
Cool; makes 24 brownies.

title: pound it almost instant dessert
directions: Mix everything, but cake.
Spread on pound cake slices.
Broil slowly until bubbly.
Garnish with cherry dipped in marmalade and rolled in coconut.

title: strawberry-nut bread
directions: Puree strawberries and pour into small pan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool. Combine dry ingredients.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs and beat until very light.
Alternately add flour mixture and water on low speed of mixer.
Stir in pureed strawberries and stir in nuts. Spread in a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Test with toothpick.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan. Wrap with foil and keep at room temperature.
Tastes better the next day.
Freezes well.

title: delightful fruit compote
directions: Stir fruits together. In microwave, heat apple jelly and water for 45 seconds or until jelly is melted. Drizzle over fruit and stir. Refrigerate.

title: three pepper catsup
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add onion, pepper, jalapenos, garlic and thyme. Cover and cook until vegetables are tender (about 10 minutes).
Mix in catsup, tomatoes and pepper.
Cover and simmer until thick (about 5 minutes). Cover and chill.
Makes about 2 3/4 cups.
Keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Excellent on hamburgers and hot dogs.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Drain pineapple; add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: pecan ozarks
directions: Place sugar and egg whites on slow fire and beat until warm. Remove from fire and continue beating until mixture stands firm; fold in nuts.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 12 minutes or until firm.

title: baked squash
directions: Combine ingredients with whisk.
Crush Wasa crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: louisiana beans and rice(serve as a side dish or in larger servings as a main dish.)
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish, combine oil, onion, green pepper, garlic, thyme and oregano.
Cover with lid; microwave on High for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once during cooking.
Stir in beans, soup, ham and red pepper.
Cover; microwave on High for 5 minutes or until hot. Stir.
Reduce power to 50%.
Cover; microwave 15 minutes or until flavors are blended.
Serve over rice.
Makes about 5 cups or 5 servings.

title: gourmet string beans
directions: Drain beans and wrap 5 or
at
a
time
with
bacon. Place in a casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain grease.
Add soups, water and 1 cup cheese.
Cook spaghetti and add to mixture.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In baking dish, add ingredients by layers and top with more cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake for diabetics
directions: Cook raisins in water until water disappears.
Add applesauce, eggs, Sweeta and oil.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into one large greased loaf pan or two small ones.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. This is like good raisin bread.

title: southern maryland oyster stew
directions: Place oysters in saucepan, add water and cook until oysters are plump and edges curl.
Remove oysters and add to milk.
Add salt and pepper, then strained oyster juice.
Add butter, heat and serve with crackers.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch.
Boil until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and sprinkle dry jello over hot mixture and stir quickly.
Pour in strawberries and mix.
Pour into cooled pie shell; refrigerate.
Also good using blueberries and blackberry jello.

title: cranberry sauce (for ham)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Heat over low heat, mixing occasionally.
Pour over baked ham slices.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Arrange chicken in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish with the meatier portions along the edge.
Combine remaining ingredients, stir well, and pour over the chicken.
Cover with wax paper and place in the microwave.
Cook on High for 12 minutes, and then on Medium-low for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.

title: carrots and grapes
directions: Cut carrots into 1-inch thick diagonal slices.
In saucepan over medium heat, cook carrots, orange juice, olive oil, salt, sugar and ginger to boiling.
Cover and simmer on low for 15 minutes.
Add cut grapes to mixture and cook 5 minutes more until carrots are fork tender.
Drain and serve.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix large container of Cool Whip and 1 box instant vanilla pudding together for cake topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pennsylvania jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water 5 minutes and cool.
Cream together eggs, sugar, vanilla and margarine.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Sift dry ingredients twice.
Add to creamed mixture a little at a time, beating thoroughly.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Add raisins and juice in which they were cooked and stir with wooden spoon.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes in 375° oven.
Makes about 5 dozen delicious cookies.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Put in large casserole dish.
Add beans, stir in barbecue sauce.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cream circle fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cream and margarine in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil, then boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add vanilla chips and marshmallow cream. Stir until melted. (Remove 1 cup of mixture and set aside.) Add flavoring and food coloring. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. (Pour cup of mixture which was saved on top) and swirl throughout with a knife. Cool for at least 2 hours in refrigerator before cutting.

title: pina colada cake
directions: In a large bowl combine
all ingredients and blend with mixer until pineapple segments
are
broken into small pieces. Pour into a greased and floured 9
x 12-inch or use two 9-inch round pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff for 60
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden brown. Add ground beef and cook until browned, stirring occasionally. Blend in remaining ingredients, except sour cream. Heat until bubbling. Just before serving, stir in sour cream. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, carrots, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Bake one hour at 350° in greased and floured tube pan.

title: heart smart meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure 1 cup of stewed tomatoes, puree in blender (save remainder).
Combine all ingredients except ground beef; mix well.
Add ground beef; mix lightly but thoroughly. Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Before last 15 minutes of baking, add remainder of stewed tomatoes to top of meat loaf.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: sausage balls
directions: Make Stove Top stuffing as per package directions and set aside to cool.
In skillet break up sausage and fry until brown (as you would ground meat).
Place on paper towels to drain away fat and allow to cool.
When both stuffing and sausage are cool, combine in large bowl.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place balls on cookie (ungreased) sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot or cold with finger foods for snack.
Toothpicks may be placed in sausage balls.

title: larry's fudge
directions: Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly, sugar, milk, salt and cocoa.
Cook to 235°.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter, but do not stir.
Cool to 110°.
Add nuts if desired. Beat with wooden spoon until loses its gloss.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan immediately.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Melt butter in pan (iron skillet).
Add brown sugar and 1 tablespoon of juice.
Add syrup to water to make 1/2 cup; set aside.
Arrange pineapple in bottom of pan.
Cream together the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the 1/2 cup reserved pineapple juice, beating after each addition.
Spread over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Invert plate.
Serve warm.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, heat oil. Saut onion, green pepper, mushrooms, garlic, basil, thyme, paprika, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Blend in tomatoes, broth, tomato sauce and bay leaves; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes. Add fish and okra; simmer 5 to 8 minutes. Stir in shrimp; cook for additional 2 to 3 minutes. Remove bay leaves.

title: minted corn & rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as label directs, but do not add margarine and use only 1/2 tsp. salt.
While rice is cooking prepare dressing: In large bowl, with wire whisk, mix lemon juice, oil, pepper, and remaining 3/4 tsp. salt until blended.
Add hot rice to dressing and toss to coat.
Cool slightly, about 30 minutes, tossing occasionally.
Meanwhile in 5 quart dutch oven heat, 3 quarts water to boiling over high heat.
Add corn and cook 5 minutes. Drain. When corn is cool enough to handle, cut kernels from cob. Add corn to rice with radishes, peas, mint and chives.
Toss until evenly mixed.
If not serving right away, cover and refrigerate up to 8 hours.

title: dutch oven lasagna
directions: Heat Dutch oven.
Brown hamburg in Dutch oven.
Drain off excess fat.
Add 7 cups hot water to hamburg.
Bring to boil.
Add macaroni and cook until tender.
Add more water if necessary.
Add tomato sauce, paste and seasoning.
Heat through, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Evenly distribute cheeses over top, cover and heat through.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: hot clam and cheese dip
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and pimentos in butter for approximately 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts. Keep hot in a chafing dish.
Serve with chips, party rye bread cut into pieces or Melba toast.

title: taco chili
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add all ingredients, except chips and cheese to large pan.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Ladle into bowls.
Top with cheese and serve with chips.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain
juice
from beets and heat.
Add sugar and vinegar. Put cornstarch in a small amount of water and add to the beet mixture.
Add butter and beets.

title: butter pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour.
Add egg; beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° until set.

title: caramel corn for microwave
directions: Pop the popcorn in brown store bag in microwave oven.
Put butter, corn syrup and brown sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat (stirring).
Boil 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Mix thoroughly and pour over corn in paper bag. Shake well.
Microwave 90 seconds and shake well again; 90 seconds again and shake well.
Microwave again for 30 seconds twice and shake well both times.
Pour into large bowl. Enjoy!

title: orange gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sherbet and mix well. When partially set, add mandarin oranges and fold in Dream Whip. Pour into oiled 1 1/2-quart ring mold; chill.
Serves 8.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Dough will be stiff at first.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Roll in slightly beaten egg white and finely chopped nuts.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Remove and quickly press thumb in center.
Bake 8 more minutes.
Remove and fill center with jelly or cherry half.

title: play dough
directions: Boil water and salt; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Let cool, then knead. Store in airtight plastic containers.

title: jennifer's easy saucepan brownies
directions: Melt margarine and shortening.
Stir in cocoa.
Dissolve and remove from heat.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add sugar and flour. Stir well.
Bake in greased square pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain excess juice from all canned vegetables.
Combine vegetables; add onion, pepper and celery.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
combine sugar and liquid ingredients.
Stir and pour over vegetables.
Mix well; cover and refrigerate 8 to 10 hours.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco until fluffy.
Alternately add flour and eggs until all flour and eggs have been added, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring and 7-Up; beat well.
Pour into a cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.

title: waffle pizzas
directions: In large bowl whisk together flours, baking powder, salt, oregano, thyme, pepper and Parmesan.
In another bowl, whisk together milk and eggs until well blended.
Pour liquid ingredients over dry ingredients and stir until just combined. Fold in olive oil.
Spray waffle grids with Pam.
Spoon 1/2 cup batter onto iron.
Spread out.
Close lid and bake.
Serve topped with tomato or pizza sauce, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, olives, onions, mushrooms, etc.
Great for the kids!

title: tortilla appetite teasers
directions: Combine cheese and salsa.
Add olives, onions and seasonings. Mix well.
Spread 1/2 cup cream cheese mixture on tortilla.
Place second one on top of cheese mixture.
Spread with 1/2 cup cheese mixture and top with third tortilla.
Start over and repeat to make a second stack.
Cover each with plastic wrap and chill.
Cut each stack into 8 triangles.
Serve with additional salsa, if desired.
Makes 16 snacks.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Place dry rice in Pyrex dish.
Salt and pepper and fry lightly the chops.
Place on top of rice and pour bouillon over.
Put one tablespoon celery and onion on each chop.
Then cover with foil. Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove foil and place one bell pepper ring on each chop; bake 10 more minutes, then serve.

title: hot potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Top with corn flakes or chips.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: divinity
directions: Mix corn syrup, sugar, water and salt in saucepan.
Cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to firm ball stage or 248° on candy thermometer.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Pour about 1/2 of the syrup slowly over whites, beating constantly. Cook remainder until 272° on thermometer or soft crack stage.
Add slowly to first mixture and beat until mixture holds its shape. Add vanilla and nuts and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter 4 1/2 minutes.
Add marshmallow and chocolate chips.
Beat until firm.
Pour in greased dish or pan.

title: crazy rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old country sausage supper
directions: In a skillet, saute the bacon until crisp; remove bacon. Saute the potatoes, onion, carrots and lima beans in the remaining drippings until tender.
Stir in the sausage; heat until meat is hot.
Garnish with bacon.
Serve in skillet.
Serves 4.

title: caramel corn pops
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal and nuts in a greased, large, shallow baking pan.
In a saucepan, bring butter, sugar and corn syrup to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove form heat; add vanilla and soda.
Pour caramel mixture over cereal and nuts; stir well.
Bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour onto waxed paper and break apart; allow to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yields approximately 10 cups of snack mix.

title: blueberry cake
directions: One half cup of the flour should be sprinkled over blueberries.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla; beat.
Add 2 eggs and beat.
Fold in floured blueberries.
Spread mixture in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over top of mixture, sprinkle generously a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Serve warm with butter or cold.
Either way it's delicious.

title: rice salad
directions: In bowl combine all ingredients. Add dressing and toss to combine.

title: sourdough starter and bread
directions: Mix yeast with 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix sugar with 2 cups warm water and flour.
Add yeast mixture.
Let stand in glass jar covered with cloth for 5 days.

title: chocolate carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.

In large bowl, beat all ingredients, except carrots and coconut, until just blended, constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula. Increase speed to high; beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Stir in carrots and coconut.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes, until done.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt chocolate chips and butter in saucepan over low heat. Remove; add condensed milk. Stir in flour, nuts and vanilla. Cover each candy Kiss completely with 1 tablespoon dough. Place cookies 1-inch apart on cookie sheet and bake 6 to 8 minutes. Do not overbake. Remove from cookie sheet and cool. Cookies will appear soft and shiny but will become firm as they cool.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Do not peel oranges!
Cut oranges and apples into large chunks.
Place all ingredients (except marshmallows) into a food processor.
Process for one or two minutes until finely chopped and thoroughly mixed, scraping down sides of container as needed. Stir in marshmallows if desired.
Serve immediately or chill until ready to serve.

title: kifli - the easy way
directions: Cream the cream cheese with butter.
Add flour; mix well and chill for 2 hours.
Use 1/4 of dough at a time, rolling out on surface sprinkled with powdered sugar to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Put small amount of apricot jam (or other of your choice) on each square, overlap opposite corners of dough and pinch to hold.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.

title: honey butter spread
directions: Stir until well mixed; serve with hot biscuits.

title: hamburger-rice casserole
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger meat, onion and salt and pepper until meat is done.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to meat and onion mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: quick chinese chicken
directions: In a skillet with a tight fitting cover, put the chicken breasts (skin side down if skin is on), water, salt and pepper together and bring to a rolling boil.

Skim off the broth and continue to cook on moderate heat; cover tightly for 35 minutes. Remove breasts; cool, strain and measure broth (put in freezer for 10 to 15 minutes until fat comes to top and remove fat).
After chicken is cool enough to handle, remove bones and skin (if still on) and discard.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and minced onion. Drain.
Add tomato soup, mustard, ketchup and brown sugar.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: peach custard
directions: Mix together eggs, butter, sugar and flour.
Fill crust with raw peaches (sliced).
Pour mixture over peaches.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and peaches are soft.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Mix all and chill.
Will last forever in refrigerator.

title: carolina chewy's
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
Blend in flour and then add nuts.
Spoon batter into a well greased lightly floured 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 300 for 45 minutes. DO NOT OVERBAKE.
Cut into squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Keep these covered well or they will get hard.

title: linguini with white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in saucepan in the oil until it floats.
(Do not allow to brown.) Add clam juice to stop cooking.
Add salt, pepper and oregano and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add clams and half of the parsley.
Cook the linguini according to package directions and reserve 1/2 cup of the cooking water.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter with a small amount of olive oil and gently fold into the cooked and drained linguini with the reserved water and remaining parsley.
Heat the clam sauce, but do not boil. Serve over the linguini.

title: wita's arroz(spanish rice)
directions: Brown uncooked rice in oil in skillet, stirring constantly. Add onion, salt, garlic and comino; brown for 1 more minute.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cover with tight fitting lid and simmer for approximately 20 minutes or until rice is fluffy and liquid absorbed.
Do not stir rice while simmering.

title: chicken, rice and almond casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter and bread crumbs. Pat in buttered dish for baking and refrigerate overnight.
Melt butter and add to bread crumbs. Sprinkle on casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mocha cheesecake
directions: Crush cookies. Mix with margarine and press into bottom of an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan. Refrigerate.

title: moon bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir together flour, nuts, cocoa and baking powder; stir into egg mixture. Spread in bottom of
greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili-thon chili
directions: Scramble hamburger, onions and green pepper.
Drain excess fat. Add salt and pepper, chili powder, taco seasoning, bay leaves to hamburger.
Mix well.
Add tomato sauce, juice and diced tomatoes. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add pinto beans and taco sauce.
Simmer for at least 1 hour.
May add a little water, if needed.

title: summer macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together cooked macaroni, cheese, celery and onion. Combine and stir macaroni mixture, mayonnaise, vinegar and pepper together.
Chill.
Serve, garnished with pickle slices and pimientos.

title: jello applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in heating water.
Add jello and applesauce. Chill until set.
Top with Miracle Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar or NutraSweet.

title: tuna and noodle casserole
directions: In 2-quart boiling water and 1 teaspoon salt, add noodles gradually.
Cook until tender.
Drain, then rinse in cold water. Mix noodles with tuna, soup, milk and cheese.
Top with tomato slices and crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: homemade sloppy joe's
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add water, sauces, salt and pepper. Sprinkle with flour and stir in.
Simmer slowly 1 hour.
Serve on warm buns.

title: yams
directions: Place sliced potatoes in deep heavy pan.
Add sugars, syrup and butter. Then add lemon flavoring.
Cook on top of range slowly until tender and syrup is thick.

title: zucchini frittles
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by tablespoon into hot oil. Cook slowly 3 to 5 minutes.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage in a large Dutch oven.
Drain off excess fat. Add celery and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add all remaining ingredients except green peppers.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add green peppers and cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.
Serve with garlic buttered Italian bread and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: black-eyed pea dinner
directions: Crumble and cook meat in large skillet.
Remove from pan. Saute onion and pepper until onion begins to get clear.
Put meat back in pan and add peas and tomatoes.
Simmer together for 5 to 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with tossed salad and garlic bread for a complete meal.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; stir in relish and additional ingredients.
Pour in dish and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 10.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken breasts in melted butter.
Roll in Parmesan cheese. Put in buttered baking dish and bake at 350° until done. (Can sprinkle extra Parmesan cheese on top of chicken breasts.)

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make a dark brown roux of flour and grease in a heavy pot. Add vegetables and garlic; saute until soft.
Add tomato paste; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp, parsley and rice.
Simmer slowly for one hour, covered, stirring occasionally. Add shrimp; cook until done (5 to 15 minutes).
Garnish with parsley and serve over rice.

title: geri's chocolate cake
directions: Mix in saucepan, butter, cocoa and water.
Bring to boil and stir into flour and sugar mixture.
Beat eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and salt to warm mixture.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Pour Geri's Chocolate Cake Frosting over hot cake.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pour into grocery bag the unsalted popped corn.
In a 2-quart bowl mix the brown sugar, butter, white syrup and salt.
Cook on High 2 1/2 minutes; stir well.
Cook on High 2 1/2 more minutes, remove and add the soda.
Stir well.
Pour on popcorn in a sack; shake well.

title: nachos
directions: Spread beans in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread hamburger on top. Cover with next 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° until warm.
Top with sour cream.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with saved ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 400°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add Italian dressing.

title: aunt estelle's chicken dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in 3 quarts water, with salt and pepper to taste, until well done.
Cool and remove skin.
Take meat off bones and put back in broth.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring water, syrup and sugar to a boil.
Add peanuts.
Cook to 295°.
Add soda and stir.
(Cook in 3-quart boiler because when you add soda it will foam up.)
Pour on greased cookie sheets.
As soon as the edges begin to cool, start pulling and stretching the candy as you would taffy.
Break off edges as they cool and continue pulling center.

title: batter dip from pancake flour
directions: Beat together.
Good for chicken, fish, pork chops, etc.
Dip in wet batter and then roll in dry before frying.

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Beat
with
fork.
Mix	sugar
and egg first.
Then add butter and milk, then soda and flour.
Mix well.
Add berries. Stir.
Put in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dirty rice
directions: In a 5 1/2 x 3 x 2-inch bread loaf pan, mix all ingredients and cover with aluminum foil and cook in a 375° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water and drain well.
Layer cabbage alternately with cheese in greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup over cabbage and cheese.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until bubbly and crumbs are brown.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Add flour, vanilla, sour milk and hot water to the other ingredients.
Drop mixture on cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put in ungreased baking dish.
Cover with topping.

title: peach almond pie
directions: Put into unbaked pie shell and bake.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix cubed chicken, cream of chicken soup and sour cream in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix crackers, melted margarine and poppy seed in plastic bag.
Spread over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart glass baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until browned on top.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, cole slaw mixture and grapes.
Add enough lemon yogurt to moisten.
Can be served on a lettuce leaf or however desired.

title: shrimp ala marinara
directions: Heat oil in skillet; brown garlic.
Add tomatoes, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic salt and shrimp.
Cook, uncovered, for an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour over 1 pound of cooked spaghetti.
Top with grated cheese.
Buon appetito.
Serves 4.

title: italian beef
directions: Heat all ingredients except roast to boiling.
Add roast and bake at 325° until tender.
Tear apart roast and place on Italian bread.
Cover with shredded Mozzarella and some of the peppers.
I like to cook it the day before in a crock-pot.

title: ladybug cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt chips with frosting, stirring frequently, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Add food colorings; blend well.

title: kool-aid sherbet
directions: Stir sugar, Kool Aid and milk until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into shallow freezer container; cover and freeze for 1 hour or until slightly thickened.
Transfer to a mixing bowl; beat until smooth.
Return to freezer container; cover and freeze until firm. Remove from freezer about 20 minutes before serving.
Yields about 3 cups.

title: dee's mayo cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat by hand until it is mixed well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until done.
Top with your favorite icing or pour powdered sugar mixed thin with milk on top and let cool.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once and stir just until dough is mixed.
Roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam or microwave broccoli until tender.
Drain well. Combine all ingredients (except cracker crumbs) and blend with broccoli.
Put in buttered casserole dish and sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
